Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.52,0:02:16.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you turn the voice down?\NWell, the energy was very strong this morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.78,0:02:27.38,Default,,0,0,0,,And spiritual energy is too much for the human nervous system.\NIt's more comfortable to stay stupid.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.65,0:02:51.62,Default,,0,0,0,,You can just get in there and fight and kill and have a hell of a good time.\NWe realize, those of you who have been here before,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.19,0:03:02.56,Default,,0,0,0,,that nothing is causing anything.\NThe primary illusion to get over is that there is anything causing anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.25,0:03:10.21,Default,,0,0,0,,So long as you believe in causality,\Nyou will be unable to disidentify with the ego
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.21,0:03:18.46,Default,,0,0,0,,because you will presume there is a this called an I\Ncausing a that called actions or so.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.12,0:03:27.87,Default,,0,0,0,,The fastest way to make rapid spiritual progress is to meditate and realize\Nthat everything is happening spontaneously.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.65,0:03:37.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything is occurring.\NAs a natural consequence, there is an infinite field of power similar,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.71,0:03:45.46,Default,,0,0,0,,let's say, to gravity and everything\Nwithin that field responds to the field.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.09,0:03:53.63,Default,,0,0,0,,This is not causing that.\NOn the contrary, these two things are moving within the field.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.75,0:04:01.52,Default,,0,0,0,,The source of this moving this way is the field.\NThe source of this moving this way is the field.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.28,0:04:08.12,Default,,0,0,0,,This is not causing that to move.\NEverything is happening spontaneously.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.12,0:04:14.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Every word that is spoken.\NI don't know what's being spoken until I hear it.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.08,0:04:18.68,Default,,0,0,0,,You understand what I'm saying?\NYou ask me, what am I going to talk about today?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.68,0:04:22.92,Default,,0,0,0,,How would I know?\NWe make up things because the audience wants to know what you're talking about.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.92,0:04:28.48,Default,,0,0,0,,If I told him the truth, how many would come?\NHe says he doesn't know what he's going to be talking about.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.48,0:04:34.37,Default,,0,0,0,,The world can't handle reality.\NSo we make up fictions.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.37,0:04:38.37,Default,,0,0,0,,The world can't handle reality.\NSo we make up fictions.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.37,0:04:45.80,Default,,0,0,0,,The world can't handle reality.\NSo we make up fictions.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.80,0:04:52.48,Default,,0,0,0,,So they're happy.\NToday we'll talk about truth and falsehood.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.48,0:05:15.91,Default,,0,0,0,,There you go.\NThe presence of God manifests as creation.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.91,0:05:25.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Creation is what seems to perception to be a progressive unfolding.\NActually, there isn't any unfolding.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.56,0:05:38.75,Default,,0,0,0,,But that makes people happy to tell them that.\NThere is this.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.75,0:05:43.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Stopwatch is your point of observation.\NAnd there's this.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.26,0:05:49.60,Default,,0,0,0,,And there's this.\NEach movement arises out of nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.60,0:05:55.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Each movement arises out of nothing.\NThis movement did not arise out of this movement.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.68,0:05:59.72,Default,,0,0,0,,This movement did not arise out of this movement.\NInstead, this movement arose spontaneously out of nothing at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.72,0:06:03.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Instead, this movement arose spontaneously out of nothing at all.\NAnd this movement arises out of nothing at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.83,0:06:09.27,Default,,0,0,0,,And this movement arises out of nothing at all.\NBecause of the intention,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.27,0:06:13.27,Default,,0,0,0,,that intention and the presence of an infinite power called divinity,\Nthat intention and the presence of an infinite power called divinity,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.27,0:06:18.72,Default,,0,0,0,,then appears forth as such.\Nthen appears forth as such.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.72,0:06:25.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Creation is continuous.\Nevery word spoken this morning
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.33,0:06:34.25,Default,,0,0,0,,is the effulgence of creation as it appears\Nto get beyond the idea of cause and effect
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.25,0:06:40.91,Default,,0,0,0,,cause and effect is a calibrated energy field at 460\Nthat means it's an intellectualization
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.91,0:06:45.26,Default,,0,0,0,,where's our wonderful map\Nwhat would we do without our map, we'd be screwed
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.26,0:06:55.93,Default,,0,0,0,,anyway, reason, evolution\Nevolution about 450
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.93,0:07:02.58,Default,,0,0,0,,causality about 460\Nquantum mechanics about 460
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.58,0:07:09.43,Default,,0,0,0,,these are all explanations\Nbut they have no basis in
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.43,0:07:13.99,Default,,0,0,0,,subjective experiential reality\Nthey're abstractions
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.99,0:07:20.29,Default,,0,0,0,,nothing is causing anything\Nand if nothing is causing anything
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.29,0:07:31.51,Default,,0,0,0,,then evolution is a limited concept as you can see\Nlet's see if everything we've said so far is true
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.51,0:07:38.63,Default,,0,0,0,,everything we've said so far is true\Nthe absolute truth
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.63,0:07:46.32,Default,,0,0,0,,and so evolution has brought us to the point\Nwhere the first time in all of human history
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.32,0:07:53.91,Default,,0,0,0,,there is a means of discerning truth from falsehood\Nthat is such a staggering realization
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.91,0:08:02.56,Default,,0,0,0,,the first person that I'd shared my work with\Nwho I sent it to him
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.56,0:08:12.08,Default,,0,0,0,,took off two weeks and went to Europe to get over the shock\Nhe said it totally blew everything I'd ever believed in
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.08,0:08:17.58,Default,,0,0,0,,he said it totally blew everything I'd ever believed in\Ntotally recontextualized my whole life
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.58,0:08:25.30,Default,,0,0,0,,the meaning of everything\Nso it took me 30 years to even approach the subject
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.30,0:08:32.47,Default,,0,0,0,,for 30 years the presence within\Nwas never spoken of
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.47,0:08:41.85,Default,,0,0,0,,there's nothing you can say about it\Nand in the 90s arose a means of explaining spiritual reality
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.85,0:08:54.07,Default,,0,0,0,,in ways that are definable and describable and verifiable\Nso then that came about
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.07,0:08:55.92,Default,,0,0,0,,as a means of explaining spiritual reality\Nthe writing of power versus force
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.92,0:09:03.47,Default,,0,0,0,,and the impact of that information is overwhelming\Nsort of like the discovery of electricity
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.47,0:09:09.37,Default,,0,0,0,,or the computer chip or the compass\Nthe telescope, the microscope
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.37,0:09:16.26,Default,,0,0,0,,because it was a new instant with which to examine\Neverything mankind believes
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.26,0:09:24.15,Default,,0,0,0,,or has believed throughout history\Nit was a way of discovering that
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.44,0:09:27.97,Default,,0,0,0,,just think in the middle ages\Nwhere the black people
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.09,0:09:42.49,Default,,0,0,0,,plague wiped out like half of Europe or something. They didn't even know it was germs. They didn't\Nknow it was germs. They didn't know it was bad air, wicked people, all kinds of things.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.72,0:10:02.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Nobody discovered germs. There wasn't any microscope. So the discovery of the microscope\Ntotally revolutionized human life. We don't die of great plagues anymore. So an instrument
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.24,0:10:18.89,Default,,0,0,0,,to discern truth from falsehood then reveals things that are somewhat shocking and quite\Ndissimilar to common human belief. If common human belief was credible, we wouldn't have
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.89,0:10:42.00,Default,,0,0,0,,the problems that we have today. Consequently, what people believe and their opinions are\Nworth nothing. That's the happy news. Everybody is free and entitled to be wrong, and they
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.00,0:10:56.90,Default,,0,0,0,,are.\NSo all we're saying is that the plague is not caused by bad air, darkness, leaving the
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.90,0:11:11.28,Default,,0,0,0,,windows open or shut. The plague is caused by a bacillus. Oh, boy. To discover anything\Nnew usually subjects you to a good deal of hostility from large quarters. And some of
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.28,0:11:29.23,Default,,0,0,0,,the things that we'll say this morning I'm sure will do the same.\NEverything is occurring spontaneously of its own, just like the discovery of the
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.23,0:11:44.90,Default,,0,0,0,,microscope, how to tell truth from falsehood. It was a spontaneous discovery, a sudden\Nlike realization. It happened in a flash. A tenth of a second I saw it instantly. And
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.90,0:11:59.63,Default,,0,0,0,,then when we begin to apply it to common human problems, we get a different viewpoint of\Nwhat the problem is all about. And so before we can solve a problem, what the world calls
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.63,0:12:12.37,Default,,0,0,0,,a problem, we first have to be able to define it.\NIn medicine, we call that diagnosis. So this morning we'll do some diagnostic work, and
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.37,0:12:31.10,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought we would start with one that's quite prominent in the world today. Before we do\Nthat, however, there's a gentleman in the audience who I have challenged to a duel.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.10,0:12:45.58,Default,,0,0,0,,In order to do this correctly, I have to have a gentleman. Come up, gentleman. Has to be\Na bona fide gentleman. And in my bag is something you're going to need to see. And the gentleman,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.58,0:13:04.35,Default,,0,0,0,,the gentleman will stand there, and I will stand here. You're going to need that. All right.\NWe are going to have a duel. You stand here, Susie, and wear your thing. All right. When
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.35,0:13:33.19,Default,,0,0,0,,she goes like this, do a practice. She does the white scarf, we will, bang! We'll practice.\NBang! So we will keep our gun store aside, and when Susie gives us the go-ahead, we'll
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.19,0:13:36.41,Default,,0,0,0,,see if we can kill each other. Okay?\NAre you ready, Susie?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.41,0:13:38.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NGet ready with it. Bang!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.41,0:13:40.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Now we're going to...\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.61,0:14:01.61,Default,,0,0,0,,And now we're going to have a fight with the daggers. But here, you come over here,\Nback up this way. Okay. All right. Now, this way. Now we will take four steps forward,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.61,0:14:24.16,Default,,0,0,0,,and then turn and fight. Okay? Go! Okay, let's put War and Peace up. Now that we've gotten\Nrid of that stupid thing, we're going to do the next one. We're going to do the next one.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.16,0:14:45.75,Default,,0,0,0,,You're a stupid idiot.\NYou understand the causes of war. Peace is the natural state when truth prevails, and
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.75,0:15:05.79,Default,,0,0,0,,war is the state when falsehood prevails. So the opposite of peace is not war. The opposite\Nof peace is falsehood. To eliminate falsehood, you have no war. That's why the propagators
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.79,0:15:23.82,Default,,0,0,0,,of falsehood are so vociferous. That looks a little fuzzy.\NWhy do we keep ringing?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.82,0:15:36.58,Default,,0,0,0,,War and Peace.\NSo peace is not something you can cause. Peace parades don't cause peace. Everybody's
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.58,0:15:48.62,Default,,0,0,0,,for peace. You know what I'm saying? Peace parades are dangerous. They're too dangerous\Nto go to. I don't want to go to a peace demonstration. There's dogs, police, people knocking each
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.62,0:16:01.82,Default,,0,0,0,,other over the head, being dragged off to jail. It's violent. Peace demonstrations\Nare too violent for me. I don't want anything to do with them. You're safer in your regiment.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.82,0:16:12.54,Default,,0,0,0,,You're safer in your regiment than you are in a peace demonstration. Nobody's getting\Nyou with clubs arresting you. There's no dogs biting your legs. The basis of war is
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.54,0:16:30.66,Default,,0,0,0,,ignorance, and the basic problem is that men cannot tell truth from falsehood. The consequences\Npolitically is that because they cannot tell truth from falsehood, the populace cannot
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.66,0:16:41.55,Default,,0,0,0,,tell a leader from a megalomaniac. The same phenomena happens over and over and over. If\Nit isn't Genghis Khan, it's Caesar or Napoleon.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.55,0:17:00.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Or Hitler or Mussolini or Hirohito. It's one megalomaniac after another. The basic\Nproblem is that people worship a political leader instead of God. Your allegiance is
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.42,0:17:16.45,Default,,0,0,0,,due only to God. Therefore, to pledge allegiance to the Fuhrer or to the State or to Saddam\Nor anybody else already puts you in a non-integrist condition. Those who worship anything but
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.45,0:17:41.14,Default,,0,0,0,,God are below 200, because that is a basic falsehood. You cannot be integrist and worship\Nthat which is secular. You can pursue it. You can even reverence money. Holy money.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.14,0:17:51.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, we're going to get to business later today. It's a tough day. Today we're starting\Nwith war and we're ending up with business, and then we're getting on to science, and
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.74,0:18:04.00,Default,,0,0,0,,oh boy.\NSomeday, the citizens have no capacity to tell truth from falsehood. Therefore, they
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.00,0:18:19.22,Default,,0,0,0,,are easily propagandized. Why? Because of the intrinsic, the trap for mankind is the\Nintrinsic innocence of consciousness. As we've described before, the nature of the human
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.22,0:18:34.66,Default,,0,0,0,,mind is like a computer. The basic consciousness is like the hardware of the computer. You\Ncan program anything into it, and the ego, then, is all the software that's been programmed
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.66,0:18:47.54,Default,,0,0,0,,into it. Forgive them, for they know not what they do is a fact. They don't know what they're\Ndoing. If they think they're honoring God by killing innocent citizens, we say how pathetic,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.54,0:19:02.23,Default,,0,0,0,,but they don't know any better. Okay. So, we come out with compassion, then. If somebody\Nkills you out of some mistaken belief, you bless them. You say, brother, you're going
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.23,0:19:21.45,Default,,0,0,0,,to die. You bless them. You say, brother, I forgive you, right? And thank you for taking\Nme out of this vale of tears. Okay. So, innocence is easily programmed into polarized ego positions.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.45,0:19:34.44,Default,,0,0,0,,As Goebbels was the master of that, I once calibrated him. He was like 40 or something.\NBut what he documented is if you repeat a lie often enough, you program people, and
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.44,0:19:49.88,Default,,0,0,0,,they will believe the lie, no matter how outrageous it is. Leave everything and go out in the\Ndesert, and the UFOs will pick you up. They do that. Thousands of the time. Okay. So,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.88,0:20:07.38,Default,,0,0,0,,we have a different way now. Let's remove all opinion. The way to enlightenment is not\Nthrough opinionation. I guarantee that. It's through divine stupidity. When you realize
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.38,0:20:22.35,Default,,0,0,0,,the limitation of the mind, you see, the mind can only know about something. It cannot\Nknow anything. To know anything, you have to be it. The only thing in my household that
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.35,0:20:47.98,Default,,0,0,0,,knows a cat is my cat. I can know about the cat, and over time, we learn more about cats,\Nbut only kitty knows kitty. No. To know, you have to be that. The world that we talk about
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.98,0:20:58.31,Default,,0,0,0,,is the world of science and power.\NThe world of politics and the daily newspaper. All these opinions. On the one side, we hear
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.31,0:21:14.84,Default,,0,0,0,,the doves, and on the other side, the wolves. What is it? Doves and eagles, foxes, eagles\Nand hawks. Eagles and hawks. Okay. No, no, not eagles and hawks. Doves and hawks. You
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.84,0:21:32.50,Default,,0,0,0,,have the doves. If you don't vote for peace, I'll kill you. Okay. And you got the hawks.\NKill them. Throughout the lectures, we've shown how the
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.50,0:21:53.19,Default,,0,0,0,,world evolves out of animal instincts. What you see is a display of animal nature as it\Nis acted out within the human domain. Territoriality being one of it. Major ones, dominance, the
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.19,0:22:09.85,Default,,0,0,0,,dominant cat fighting for territoriality. So, the daily headlines are not much different\Nthan the wilds of Africa or 40 million years ago. You just see one species fighting for
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.85,0:22:27.81,Default,,0,0,0,,more space. And mating opportunities. They seem to be obsessed with mating. And food\Nand dominance. And therefore, you kill anything that invades your space. In 40 million years,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:27.81,0:22:44.03,Default,,0,0,0,,however, things change. Not much, huh? Oh, God. We don't have fur. That's one of the\Nmain distinctions between us people. Just a little fur. Not much.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:45.83,0:22:58.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay. So, let's say we don't know anything about this world. We come from some other\Nstar. And we say, let's study what these people are all about. And the only instrument we
Dialogue: 0,0:22:58.81,0:23:11.57,Default,,0,0,0,,have is a way to tell truth from false, other than that we don't know anything about these\Npeople here. So, what happens if we calibrate? Let's put opinion aside. You can save your
Dialogue: 0,0:23:11.57,0:23:26.41,Default,,0,0,0,,booze for later and your cheers for later. The doves and the hawks can take turns. Doves\Nand then hawks. I'm going to do it that way. Okay. If we just calibrate, let's say we don't
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.41,0:23:45.75,Default,,0,0,0,,care about personalities. President Bush's address to the Congress, the annual address\Nwas 460. Secretary Powell's position in all this war, and this is 460. The Secretary of
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.75,0:24:01.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Defense is 460. The U.S. military, 450. The U.S. military, 460. The U.S. military, 450.\NThe U.S. State Department, 450. That's their intention. The solicitude for the unintended
Dialogue: 0,0:24:01.50,0:24:18.18,Default,,0,0,0,,victims of all this, the reluctance to take, even have it happen. So, in the mid-400s,\Nthe mid-400s is about the highest you can expect in ordinary life. The presidency of
Dialogue: 0,0:24:18.18,0:24:34.22,Default,,0,0,0,,the United States calibrates around 450 to 460. So, whoever fills that void is going\Nto have a different role than whatever the circumstances. This is the level of the intellect.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:34.22,0:24:53.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Reason, meaning, wisdom, beginning of wisdom. The Supreme Court calibrates about 480. So,\Nthis has to do with reason, logic, thinking a thing through, understanding, the capacity
Dialogue: 0,0:24:53.25,0:25:06.10,Default,,0,0,0,,to abstract concepts, ethics.\NSo, 460 is the rule of ethics, reason, balance, doing the intelligent, expected thing, and
Dialogue: 0,0:25:06.10,0:25:22.09,Default,,0,0,0,,fulfilling one's obligations. I do a lot of radio programs and they tend to be quite polarized\Npolitically. And they always get mad when they say, well, what does President Bush calibrate
Dialogue: 0,0:25:22.09,0:25:34.34,Default,,0,0,0,,at? Well, he calibrates at 460. Oh, that can't be. Everybody's mad at that. The presidency\Nof the United States, to get there and to handle it, you better be around 450 or 460.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:34.34,0:25:49.55,Default,,0,0,0,,You couldn't handle it otherwise. The high 500s, you'd be out of it. In the high 500s,\Nyou wouldn't be able to handle all that, power brokering and detail and all. So, the ideal
Dialogue: 0,0:25:49.55,0:26:03.56,Default,,0,0,0,,president, the ideal president at this time would be around 460. That would be ideal.\NI think the highest president we've ever had was 499. To be able to handle it all, you've
Dialogue: 0,0:26:03.56,0:26:20.36,Default,,0,0,0,,got to be around 460. The Supreme Court calibrates at 480. The Supreme Court is not on the firing\Nline. They're into philosophizing and intellect and reason and learnedness. It's a little
Dialogue: 0,0:26:20.36,0:26:30.84,Default,,0,0,0,,bit too academic at 480 to be president of the United States. You can't be that academic.\NYou have to be able to relate to the people. You can't be too high or you become sort of
Dialogue: 0,0:26:30.84,0:26:42.42,Default,,0,0,0,,ivory tower intellectualism.\NSo, we'd say, actually, that's pretty ideal. All right. The Congress itself is at 450.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:42.42,0:26:59.25,Default,,0,0,0,,The United States population has been at 431. I didn't recalibrate it. The U.S. media has\Na different mission at 320. The 400s are a little bit too intellectual for the public.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:59.25,0:27:17.73,Default,,0,0,0,,So, if you're going to do a TV show, you've got to bring it down to closer to the populace.\NAnd what happened to the – oh. Okay. The U.S. media is around 320. In the new book
Dialogue: 0,0:27:17.73,0:27:33.43,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm doing, we've calibrated all the networks and network news and all the commentators\Nand Time and Newsweek and calibrated all the major media. It's like we have a new instrument
Dialogue: 0,0:27:33.43,0:27:37.43,Default,,0,0,0,,with which to study civilization.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:37.43,0:27:52.42,Default,,0,0,0,,And that's what this new book is about, studying every aspect of human civilization\Nfrom its early onset to its present presentations, everything included, from the Polk to the Dixie
Dialogue: 0,0:27:52.42,0:28:03.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Chicks.\NAll right. So, the media has to be – you can't be too erudite, and you'll notice that
Dialogue: 0,0:28:03.44,0:28:12.79,Default,,0,0,0,,when you look at the editorial page.\NAll right.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:12.79,0:28:30.08,Default,,0,0,0,,In this whole thing that's going on, we have the peace vigils. As I said, peace protest\Nparades calibrate pretty low. But peace vigils are 305, and 300 is goodwill. Goodwill, willingness,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:30.08,0:28:42.50,Default,,0,0,0,,it's benign. A peace vigil is benign. It threatens no one. We're supposed to have\Nfreedom of expression. So, there you express yourself, but you're not trying to coerce
Dialogue: 0,0:28:42.50,0:28:55.61,Default,,0,0,0,,other people or force them to think your way. You're not trying to proselytize. You\Nstand there and you make a statement, like a mudra. A mudra makes a statement non-verbally,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:55.61,0:29:11.22,Default,,0,0,0,,but you're not trying to coerce others by your statement.\NThe UN Security Council calibrates it 202. It's not a star in this whole thing, but
Dialogue: 0,0:29:11.22,0:29:22.29,Default,,0,0,0,,it hangs on to integrity.\NSo, 200 is integrity. 202 is the level of functionalism. Many government agencies calibrate
Dialogue: 0,0:29:22.29,0:29:38.27,Default,,0,0,0,,it 202, many of them, the IRS. That's bureaucratic functionalism. And 202 is the waitress who\Ntakes your order, but she doesn't smile and she don't remember you, and you don't feel
Dialogue: 0,0:29:38.27,0:29:46.14,Default,,0,0,0,,compelled to return to that restaurant. I mean, I want somebody that says, hi, doc, the\Nregular.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:46.14,0:29:48.14,Default,,0,0,0,,There.\NThat's sort of a liveness.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:48.14,0:30:01.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, 202 is you crawl up and you get a message. If you want so-and-so, press 1. If you want\Nso-and-so, press 2. You press 2, and now you've got a whole new menu. You go down to that
Dialogue: 0,0:30:01.91,0:30:13.20,Default,,0,0,0,,menu, now press 6. So, it's functional, but it's not exactly warm, you know?\NAll right. So, the UN Security Council did not really warm the cockles of my heart, the
Dialogue: 0,0:30:13.20,0:30:16.94,Default,,0,0,0,,way they handled this whole thing.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:16.94,0:30:27.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, we keep on examining this.\NAnd we come to the revelation of some other phenomena in calibrating the energy levels
Dialogue: 0,0:30:27.42,0:30:31.57,Default,,0,0,0,,of everything in the world.\NWow.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:31.57,0:30:38.33,Default,,0,0,0,,I feel like I'm rewriting the Encyclopedia Britannica.\NI'm only up to M already.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:38.33,0:30:42.24,Default,,0,0,0,,So, anyway, what were we going to say?\NOh, yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:42.24,0:30:48.24,Default,,0,0,0,,What I wanted to do for these lectures, and I haven't gotten to it yet, is a map of the\Nworld.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:48.24,0:30:50.24,Default,,0,0,0,,I need, like, two slides.\NOne this side of the world and one slide this side of the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:50.24,0:31:03.46,Default,,0,0,0,,And you calibrate the energy levels of the different continents, the different countries,\Ndifferent locations, and you'll find that much like human, I mean, much like animal
Dialogue: 0,0:31:03.46,0:31:16.46,Default,,0,0,0,,species, mankind, certain species tend to congregate together.\NYou'll find areas of the world, such as America, 431.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:16.46,0:31:23.00,Default,,0,0,0,,We take 431 for granted.\N431 is amazingly high.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:23.00,0:31:34.00,Default,,0,0,0,,431 means that you give reason priority over emotion.\NAs you get down around the 200s and below 200, emotion is what counts.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:34.00,0:31:40.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Hatred is more important than reason.\NNo, we're constrained by reason.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:40.08,0:31:46.53,Default,,0,0,0,,That was the gentleman's fault that I killed before.\NHe's constrained by honesty and reason.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:46.53,0:31:53.67,Default,,0,0,0,,You see how deadly it is?\NBecause I'm a street fighter.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:53.67,0:31:58.38,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't have a knife in the guy before he's ready for the goal.\NYou understand?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:58.38,0:32:01.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Because I play to win.\NIn the street, you play to win.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:01.07,0:32:17.82,Default,,0,0,0,,This world is not run by Marquis of Queensberry rules.\NNow we get to, we left the Marquis of Queensberry rules up here.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:17.82,0:32:22.96,Default,,0,0,0,,These people are run by the Marquis of Queensberry rules.\NThey all went to college.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:22.96,0:32:29.38,Default,,0,0,0,,They all think that a thing is fair or not fair.\NIn street fighting, whoever heard of fair?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:29.38,0:32:32.89,Default,,0,0,0,,In the jungle, whoever heard of fair?\NFair?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:32.89,0:32:38.40,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you mean fair?\NNot fair to eat a little cub?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:38.40,0:32:41.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Why not?\NIt's delicious.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:41.75,0:32:53.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Different law.\NThe law of the jungle is not the law of the Harvard rowing team.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:53.04,0:33:03.38,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.\NSo now if we turn the, if we shift the slide, which I haven't done yet, to other continents,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:03.38,0:33:10.57,Default,,0,0,0,,you'll find that whole continents calibrate incredibly low.\NLet's do Africa as a continent.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:10.57,0:33:17.53,Default,,0,0,0,,We have permission to do Africa as a continent.\NIt's over 40, 50, 60.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:17.53,0:33:35.42,Default,,0,0,0,,The whole continent, 70.\NIf we're in the western continent, the places I've been, it's obvious at first sight that
Dialogue: 0,0:33:35.42,0:33:41.71,Default,,0,0,0,,they calibrate below 70.\NThe poverty in some areas of South America is absolutely stunning.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:41.71,0:33:47.82,Default,,0,0,0,,People talk about poverty in the United States, they haven't the slightest idea what poverty\Nis.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:47.82,0:33:57.52,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.\NNow if we look at the Middle East, which historically has been at war for thousands
Dialogue: 0,0:33:57.52,0:34:07.14,Default,,0,0,0,,of years, and still is, now we get different calibrations.\NWe see Iran 185, Palestine 180, and Israel 180.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:07.14,0:34:17.92,Default,,0,0,0,,So here you got two 180s, both below integrity.\NThey can pontificate all they want, but frankly, they calibrate 180.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:17.92,0:34:22.75,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.\NPeace demonstrations, unfortunately, as I said, are too violent for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:22.75,0:34:26.88,Default,,0,0,0,,They only calibrate 170.\NBecause they represent force.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:26.88,0:34:39.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything below 200 is force.\NTrying to force others to see it your way, forced by intimidation, forced by demonstration,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:39.32,0:34:45.26,Default,,0,0,0,,like the Ku Klux Klan.\NBy demonstration, intimidate.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:45.26,0:34:50.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NTurkey calibrates at 165.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:50.17,0:34:53.17,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a waffling country, isn't it?\NIt waffles.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:53.17,0:34:58.21,Default,,0,0,0,,The Iraqi population is 140.\NThe Iraq media is 140.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:58.21,0:35:06.92,Default,,0,0,0,,France, who is in bed with these people, not surprisingly, calibrates their political position\Nis also 140.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:06.92,0:35:14.19,Default,,0,0,0,,The Syrian regime, at this point, is 130.\NThese have made change over time.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:14.19,0:35:24.65,Default,,0,0,0,,A couple thousand years, even.\NThe consciousness level of mankind stood at 190.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:24.65,0:35:32.03,Default,,0,0,0,,At the time of Jesus, it was 100.\NAnd by the Middle Ages, by the year 1200, 1420.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:32.03,0:35:37.03,Default,,0,0,0,,By the year 1200, 1400.\NOn up to the late 1980s, it was 190.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:37.03,0:35:44.53,Default,,0,0,0,,The whole world was non-integrist.\NHuman history is not pleasant to look at.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:44.53,0:35:56.03,Default,,0,0,0,,In the storybooks of history, they pick out the flowers that survived.\NMozart, the great heroes, etc.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:56.03,0:36:04.69,Default,,0,0,0,,But that was unusual.\NIt was so unusual that it's in the history books.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:04.69,0:36:13.98,Default,,0,0,0,,If it was usual, it wouldn't be in the history books, would it?\NSyria, right now, 130.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:13.98,0:36:22.32,Default,,0,0,0,,The Middle East in general, the whole Middle East as a region of the world,\Nif we just do a world map, is 110.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:22.32,0:36:35.46,Default,,0,0,0,,110.\NNow, you expect peace in a region that calibrates at 110?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:35.46,0:36:43.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Billification of the U.S. and the presidency has become a common political positionality.\NHmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:43.53,0:36:48.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Non-integrist for reasons that we will get into later.\NIt calibrates at 70.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:48.53,0:36:56.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Saddam Hussein, God bless him, is 65.\NAnd the Iraq military leaders are 65.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:56.71,0:37:01.05,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.\NThe real worry, the real worry in the world is jihad.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:01.05,0:37:08.53,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the real worry.\NIt sets up the entire Muslim, Arabic, Middle East world against the rest of the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:08.53,0:37:17.17,Default,,0,0,0,,That is the real, that is the real worry.\NOf course, it takes expression in Saddam Hussein.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:17.17,0:37:30.38,Default,,0,0,0,,And Iraq and bin Laden and various things like that.\NBut to declare war against the rest of the world, then, is causing a deep division.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:30.38,0:37:40.57,Default,,0,0,0,,So jihad, in my view of it, is the most serious threat to peace in the whole world.\NThe Islamic terrorists are just coming out of this.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:40.57,0:37:58.13,Default,,0,0,0,,And the Taliban at 45 and bin Laden at 40 are the expression of that.\NThe energies of war, let's see.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:58.13,0:38:05.03,Default,,0,0,0,,The energies of war, we can look at fallacy.\NWe said that the enemy of war was falsehood.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:05.03,0:38:09.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Falsehood.\NThe enemies of war are falsehood.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:09.40,0:38:17.50,Default,,0,0,0,,And they become politically expressed.\NThe far left is Luciferic and the far right is Satanic.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:17.50,0:38:30.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And there you have the display of non-integrity.\NLuciferic then denies the sovereignty of God and seeks grandiose control over others.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:30.00,0:38:37.09,Default,,0,0,0,,And to do so, it distorts logic and truth.\NIt's the great enemy of truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:37.09,0:38:44.42,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the Trojan horse in the newest book I did.\NHow many of you have read I?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:44.42,0:38:51.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, so there's a certain familiarity.\NThe Trojan horse is to first present the lie.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:51.09,0:39:03.71,Default,,0,0,0,,And I presented the lie to you before, this morning.\NThe two of us had a duel.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:03.71,0:39:14.15,Default,,0,0,0,,He's an honest, integrous gentleman.\NSitting duck.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:14.15,0:39:24.84,Default,,0,0,0,,You saw it happen, right?\NSo you saw a recapitulation of what led into World War I, World War II, and every other war.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:24.84,0:39:40.19,Default,,0,0,0,,I grew up, you know, World War I has just ended and the veterans with battle shock and all were staggering around.\NAnd World War II was now arising.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:40.19,0:39:53.09,Default,,0,0,0,,And then the obvious danger was ignored.\NThe League of Nations was about as effective as the UN is now.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:53.09,0:40:03.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Did nothing at all.\NAs this giant war machine built up, the greatest war machine the world has ever seen, built up right on the doorstep of Europe.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:03.09,0:40:21.65,Default,,0,0,0,,At that time, there was all kinds of vociferous protest about peace and isolationism.\NLindbergh and Charlie Chaplin, all kinds of people got up there.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:21.65,0:40:30.21,Default,,0,0,0,,But the actual diplomatic negotiation was handled by Neville Chamberlain.\NYeah?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:30.21,0:40:41.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Neville Chamberlain at the time calibrated at 180.\NSo this morning we played the part of Hitler versus Neville Chamberlain.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:41.55,0:40:56.05,Default,,0,0,0,,I was Hitler and he was Neville Chamberlain.\NA gentleman who believed that I would be bound by a non-aggression treaty.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:56.05,0:41:09.30,Default,,0,0,0,,So Neville Chamberlain went to meet with Hitler and they signed a non-aggression treaty.\NAnd he came back with a signed peace in our times.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:09.30,0:41:27.30,Default,,0,0,0,,At the same time, Churchill saw that the truth of it was that this guy is a gangster, is going to laugh at a contract, and he's building up a giant war machine for what?\NNot just for entertainment.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:27.30,0:41:34.44,Default,,0,0,0,,So Churchill was vilified as a war monger.\NWar monger.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:34.44,0:41:46.01,Default,,0,0,0,,To be saying these kind of things.\NThe price, then, of the Trojan horse, of the fallacy of peace, which calibrated at 180.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:46.01,0:41:53.63,Default,,0,0,0,,At the time.\NCost 70 million lives.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:53.63,0:42:03.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Though political opinion is not all that innocent, is it?\N70 million people dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:03.76,0:42:08.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Blown to bits.\NTheir homes blown to bits.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:08.21,0:42:14.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Their country blown to bits.\NDresden, Cologne, all the magnificent beauty of medieval Europe destroyed.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:14.23,0:42:29.05,Default,,0,0,0,,The inability to tell a megalomaniac from a leader.\NSo the Trojan horse, then, is the doorstep.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:29.05,0:42:44.94,Default,,0,0,0,,The doors to war are opened by a consciousness level of 180, which distorts truth because it's in denial about human nature.\NIt's some kind of a schoolboy, Girl Scouts view of things.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:44.94,0:43:01.32,Default,,0,0,0,,If we just be nice to them, they will change.\NIn World War II, I was in dives in Shanghai waterfront.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:01.32,0:43:12.90,Default,,0,0,0,,And for entertainment, the war was just over, so suddenly there was no excitement going on.\NSo the crew would go ashore and get into fights in various bars.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:12.90,0:43:19.50,Default,,0,0,0,,I had two cronies.\NOne was Big Red Hawkins, who played in for Pennsylvania.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:19.50,0:43:27.30,Default,,0,0,0,,He was about six foot five and weighed 290 pounds of solid muscle.\NA walking battering ram.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:27.30,0:43:32.61,Default,,0,0,0,,And red hair.\NAnd he quickly got angry.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:32.61,0:43:42.30,Default,,0,0,0,,The other guy was Jimmy Sanders, who was not all that tall.\NJimmy Sanders was a bosun's mate.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:42.30,0:43:49.88,Default,,0,0,0,,And he was champion of the third fleet.\NDeadly.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:49.88,0:43:57.36,Default,,0,0,0,,When I went on that ship, which is a minesweeper, the bosun says to me,\NHey shorty, you know how to box?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:57.36,0:44:06.48,Default,,0,0,0,,I said, gee, I took lessons with Richie Mitchell, who had been the former medium weight champion.\NHave I told you this story before?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:06.48,0:44:09.53,Default,,0,0,0,,No, sorry.\NSo I'm a new recruit.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:09.53,0:44:14.98,Default,,0,0,0,,I was sent out on hazardous duty.\NAnyway, I'm the new recruit.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:14.98,0:44:24.90,Default,,0,0,0,,So Sanders says, well, let's do a couple of rounds in the gun tub.\NSo I go into the gun tub with him.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:24.90,0:44:29.90,Default,,0,0,0,,We put on the gloves.\NAnd he knocked me cold with one sock in the jaw.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:29.90,0:44:37.51,Default,,0,0,0,,One shot and I was cold.\NThen they told me after, he was the champion of the third fleet.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:37.51,0:44:43.55,Default,,0,0,0,,He was deadly.\NSo fast you couldn't see him move.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:43.55,0:44:51.65,Default,,0,0,0,,He had a left jab that was so fast you didn't see it coming.\NAnd you were grogged by his left jab.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:51.65,0:44:58.65,Default,,0,0,0,,And then he hit you with the upper right.\NThis was so fast that you were jarred by it.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:58.65,0:45:06.28,Default,,0,0,0,,And while you were jarred, he hit you out.\NWell, he was something marvelous to watch, I tell you.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:06.28,0:45:13.13,Default,,0,0,0,,And we would go ashore, the three of us.\NTrouble.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:13.13,0:45:26.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I was the bait.\NSo we go in these waterfront bars.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:26.36,0:45:38.36,Default,,0,0,0,,And my role was to, you know, we had a patch.\NAnd being on a minesweep, you know, our whole crew was only 18 people.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:38.36,0:45:41.53,Default,,0,0,0,,We were all under 22.\NWe were all kids.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:41.53,0:45:46.61,Default,,0,0,0,,And so we had a minesweep.\NAnd we were in a big port there.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:46.61,0:45:54.67,Default,,0,0,0,,And there were battleships that had 2,200 guys on them, et cetera.\NSo they called us kiddie sailors.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:54.67,0:46:01.09,Default,,0,0,0,,So we'd go into this bar.\NAnd they would say, Shorty, go and talk to these people.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:01.09,0:46:05.42,Default,,0,0,0,,So I'd go up to them, sit over this.\NAnd they would sit over there.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:05.42,0:46:12.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Pretty soon, a battleship sailor would look at me and say, hey, kiddie sailor.\NImmediately, these two guys would come out of the wall.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:12.61,0:46:17.61,Default,,0,0,0,,And they'd say, hey, are you insulting my friend here?\NAnd they'd push Shorty aside.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:17.61,0:46:21.92,Default,,0,0,0,,My job was to stay the hell out of the way.\NShorty, you go over here.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:21.92,0:46:26.44,Default,,0,0,0,,And then pow, the whole place would be ripped up.\NThe mirror.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:28.53,0:46:31.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Stools flying.\NBodies flying.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:31.76,0:46:36.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Mirrors crashing.\NIt was murderous.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:36.61,0:46:40.61,Default,,0,0,0,,I only saw Jimmy Sanders.\NHe only got stopped once.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:40.61,0:46:43.61,Default,,0,0,0,,He had a guy up against the wall.\NAnd he was about to cream him.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:43.61,0:46:52.30,Default,,0,0,0,,And the guy pulled out a French 45.\NAnd he said, OK.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:52.30,0:47:00.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, he knocked me out a couple other times, too, for one thing or another.\NOne time, I went up to the top of the mast.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:00.63,0:47:03.63,Default,,0,0,0,,And he says, don't look down.\NI had a fear of heights.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:03.63,0:47:07.76,Default,,0,0,0,,He says, don't look down, Shorty.\NWell, I got all the way up to the top of the mast.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:07.76,0:47:10.76,Default,,0,0,0,,There was a paint bucket.\NAnd I made the mistake of looking down.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:10.76,0:47:15.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Instantly, the body froze to the mast.\NBeyond volition.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:15.11,0:47:20.11,Default,,0,0,0,,My body did not respond to volition.\NI tried very, very hard to let go.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:20.11,0:47:24.26,Default,,0,0,0,,And I couldn't.\NHe says, Shorty, I'll have to cold cock you.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:24.26,0:47:36.26,Default,,0,0,0,,I hope he comes in the bosun's chair.\NSo life in the arena of what's real is quite different.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:36.26,0:47:46.78,Default,,0,0,0,,It's quite different than the arena of political pretense.\NPolitical pretense.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:46.78,0:47:57.19,Default,,0,0,0,,What's deadly, then, is that that which is fallacious and presented as truth\Nnumbs you to the real truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:57.19,0:48:08.71,Default,,0,0,0,,And consequently, so the war starts with Lucifer distortion of reality.\NAnd then that opens the gates for the satanic, which is waiting.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:08.71,0:48:16.71,Default,,0,0,0,,And when the time is right, the satanic, which represents death, war, destruction,\Nrape, pillage, murder.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:16.71,0:48:30.42,Default,,0,0,0,,The rape of the then king was the satanic let loose.\NThe far left then is Luciferic.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:30.42,0:48:35.73,Default,,0,0,0,,The far right is satanic.\NThe door, nobody votes for war.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:35.73,0:48:44.38,Default,,0,0,0,,The satanic can't get elected.\NYou can't say, all you people, I want you to vote for war.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:44.38,0:48:49.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Nobody's going to vote for war.\NThe satanic doesn't win elections.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:49.05,0:48:53.92,Default,,0,0,0,,No.\NLuciferic sets the stage.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:53.92,0:48:56.92,Default,,0,0,0,,And that's the Trojan horse.\NAnd then the door opens.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:56.92,0:49:07.96,Default,,0,0,0,,And then the satanic comes out with the guns and the murder.\NSo we just want to see how war evolves.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:07.96,0:49:26.78,Default,,0,0,0,,And if that is the case, if that is the case, if the prelude to all war is the distortion\Nof truth, if all war is set by falsehood, so the enemy of war, then, is truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:26.78,0:49:32.73,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.\NAnd the essence of all the lectures we've given is that you really can't trust anything
Dialogue: 0,0:49:32.73,0:49:41.46,Default,,0,0,0,,in this whole world at all, historically or currently, unless you calibrate this level\Nof truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:41.46,0:49:50.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Why?\NBecause out of the humility, out of humility, you realize the nature of the mind is such
Dialogue: 0,0:49:50.69,0:49:59.65,Default,,0,0,0,,that it cannot tell truth from falsehood.\NYou cannot discover the cause of plague until you realize the beginning of truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:59.65,0:50:14.17,Default,,0,0,0,,And you realize, to begin with, that you do not know what the cause of plague is.\NSo long as you think it's overcrowding or night air coming into windows or something,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:14.17,0:50:22.09,Default,,0,0,0,,you won't find it.\NSo the beginning of all great discovery is humility.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:22.09,0:50:30.34,Default,,0,0,0,,The human mind is not capable of telling truth from falsehood.\NA politician doesn't become a great leader because he's stupid.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:30.34,0:50:41.21,Default,,0,0,0,,He becomes a great leader because he is extremely clever in how to persuade people and make\Nthem sound logical and reasonable.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:41.21,0:50:55.05,Default,,0,0,0,,And what the great leader appeals to is your solar plexus and your spleen.\NHitler appealed to the spleen.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:55.05,0:51:08.73,Default,,0,0,0,,And the course is always to right a wrong.\NMankind is led to slaughter by righteousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:08.73,0:51:21.48,Default,,0,0,0,,It's righteous to undo the wrong of the Versailles Treaty.\NIt could have been stopped very easily.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:21.48,0:51:30.46,Default,,0,0,0,,By the French, when he invaded the Sudetenland, that would have been a snap.\NIt would have saved 70 million lives.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:30.46,0:51:39.71,Default,,0,0,0,,But that requires integrity and the capacity to know the truth.\NSo we cannot fault mankind, present or past, because it was blind.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:39.71,0:51:46.07,Default,,0,0,0,,It didn't know the cause of plague.\NIt was simply a bacillus carried by the rat.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:46.07,0:51:52.28,Default,,0,0,0,,It's rat flea.\NIt's a bacillus that's caused and is carried by the rat flea.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:52.28,0:51:58.80,Default,,0,0,0,,So the rats don't cause the plague.\NAnd the flea doesn't cause the plague.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:58.80,0:52:12.42,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the plague bacillus carried by the flea.\NSo we start out saying, I don't know anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:12.42,0:52:20.13,Default,,0,0,0,,We only have one instrument.\NWe let you loose in this strange culture here.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:20.13,0:52:26.90,Default,,0,0,0,,We let you out of the spacecraft from this other civilization.\NAnd you only have one tool here.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:26.90,0:52:34.34,Default,,0,0,0,,And that's how to tell truth from falsehood.\NYou'd be way ahead of the game, wouldn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:34.34,0:52:40.34,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't have to do the Encyclopedia Britannica.\NYou realize when you look at the Encyclopedia Britannica,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:40.34,0:52:45.34,Default,,0,0,0,,you've got to let all of that stuff go to become enlightened.\NOh, boy.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:45.34,0:52:54.26,Default,,0,0,0,,All the belief systems, all the prevailing attitudes.\NSo we start out saying, I don't know anything about anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:54.26,0:53:07.05,Default,,0,0,0,,That makes it easier to let go of positionalities.\NThe idea that I know and the idea that I must win,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:07.05,0:53:16.11,Default,,0,0,0,,that what I think my opinion must win,\Nwhether people like it or not, is really the height of egotism.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:16.11,0:53:28.82,Default,,0,0,0,,So we see in the current political world spectacular displays of egotism.\NFreedom of speech means I can tell you what I think.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:28.82,0:53:37.44,Default,,0,0,0,,To go beyond that is to exploit the freedom of speech\Nand now to try to coerce others with moral indignation.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:37.44,0:53:45.09,Default,,0,0,0,,The weapon that's really destroying our current American society\Nand threatening the fabric of it
Dialogue: 0,0:53:45.09,0:53:53.13,Default,,0,0,0,,is the business of moral indignation,\Nwhich we'll get to later when we talk about business.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:53.13,0:54:01.21,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a new industry.\NIt's a self-propagating industry, extremely well funded,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:01.21,0:54:18.17,Default,,0,0,0,,and its basic work is one of disquietude, complaints,\Ngrievances, moral indignation.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:18.17,0:54:23.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Are we satisfied that we know that they're seeing war and peace\Nand how they come about?
Dialogue: 0,0:54:23.23,0:54:29.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Anybody have any doubts or questions?\NAnybody differs with me?
Dialogue: 0,0:54:29.69,0:54:52.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyone wishes to have a duel about the matter?\NI'd say the populace, the populace of this country at this time,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:52.34,0:54:58.84,Default,,0,0,0,,calibrates over so-and-so to get where it's at.\NI mean, there we've seen endless decades
Dialogue: 0,0:54:58.84,0:55:07.07,Default,,0,0,0,,of mutual provocation.\NAnybody who wants peace gets assassinated.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:07.07,0:55:15.32,Default,,0,0,0,,The way to have a short regiment is to...\NSo you see mutual provocation.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:15.32,0:55:22.53,Default,,0,0,0,,I think I did write about that in the book.\NAs you watch the clash, you see the provocation.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:22.53,0:55:34.90,Default,,0,0,0,,See, because all this takes us into victim, victim, perpetrator and victim.\NAll this is tied in with a whole fallacious belief system
Dialogue: 0,0:55:34.90,0:55:41.92,Default,,0,0,0,,which prevails on our society,\Nhaving to do with perpetrator and victim.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:41.92,0:55:56.80,Default,,0,0,0,,The way you start a thing off is by playing the victim,\Nyou force the perpetrator to attack you.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:56.80,0:56:09.48,Default,,0,0,0,,This is like suicide by police fire.\NI force you now so that you can take the moral blame.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:09.48,0:56:14.65,Default,,0,0,0,,I feint that I have a gun,\Nand now when the cop in self-defense shoots you,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:14.65,0:56:22.07,Default,,0,0,0,,you're the innocent victim.\NThis is an extremely non-integrist
Dialogue: 0,0:56:22.07,0:56:30.34,Default,,0,0,0,,and rather malignant development in our society.\NAnd you see how it's based on cause.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:30.34,0:56:40.09,Default,,0,0,0,,If we look at the entire world as if it was one human being,\None human being,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:40.09,0:56:45.42,Default,,0,0,0,,in the practice of medicine,\Nyou have to decide when you're going to operate on an appendix.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:45.42,0:56:50.34,Default,,0,0,0,,It's impending,\Nand if you wait too long,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:50.34,0:56:53.61,Default,,0,0,0,,the appendix will burst.\NNow you've got a real problem,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:53.61,0:56:57.61,Default,,0,0,0,,because you've got an infection,\Nand you've got peritonitis looking in the face.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:57.61,0:57:03.55,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the physician's duty\Nto anticipate an obvious process.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:03.55,0:57:09.65,Default,,0,0,0,,You can see that the appendix is getting hotter and hotter\Nand hotter and hotter.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:09.65,0:57:14.13,Default,,0,0,0,,And you know that if you don't take action,\Nit will burst,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:14.13,0:57:17.51,Default,,0,0,0,,and now you will die of peritonitis.\NYou understand?
Dialogue: 0,0:57:17.51,0:57:22.80,Default,,0,0,0,,To save the body,\Nto save the whole of mankind,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:22.80,0:57:26.80,Default,,0,0,0,,how far can a responsible person\Nlet an appendix develop?
Dialogue: 0,0:57:26.80,0:57:35.57,Default,,0,0,0,,World War II, we saw,\N70 million was the death rate
Dialogue: 0,0:57:35.57,0:57:44.26,Default,,0,0,0,,for failing to remove the appendix\Nin a timely manner.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:44.26,0:57:48.46,Default,,0,0,0,,If the League of Nations was a physician,\Nhe'd still be paying off his malpractice.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:48.46,0:57:54.78,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't wait until it ruptures\Nand costs 70 million people
Dialogue: 0,0:57:54.78,0:57:58.26,Default,,0,0,0,,or the death of the patient.\NOver and over,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:58.26,0:58:01.07,Default,,0,0,0,,my feeling,\Npeople say,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:01.07,0:58:06.67,Default,,0,0,0,,what do you think about Bush?\NMy feeling about Bush is,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:06.67,0:58:10.67,Default,,0,0,0,,he states his position publicly\Nover and over again.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:10.67,0:58:14.15,Default,,0,0,0,,If you ask him,\Nwhat is his position?
Dialogue: 0,0:58:14.15,0:58:17.40,Default,,0,0,0,,His position says,\Nhe says,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:17.40,0:58:20.88,Default,,0,0,0,,my position is 460.\NNo, no, you don't say that.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:20.88,0:58:26.65,Default,,0,0,0,,What is 460?\NHe tells you over and over again,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:26.65,0:58:33.01,Default,,0,0,0,,I took an oath of office\Nwith my hand on the Bible.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:33.01,0:58:35.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Here's a man who's recovered from the war.\NHere's a man who's recovered
Dialogue: 0,0:58:35.17,0:58:38.34,Default,,0,0,0,,from a fatal illness\Nby means of spiritual,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:38.34,0:58:44.30,Default,,0,0,0,,the reason he favors\Nspiritually oriented recovery groups.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:44.30,0:58:46.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Integrity then.\NHe says,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:46.30,0:58:50.55,Default,,0,0,0,,I took an oath on the Bible\Nto fulfill the obligation,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:50.55,0:58:53.55,Default,,0,0,0,,the oath of the President\Nof the United States of America,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:53.55,0:58:59.55,Default,,0,0,0,,which is to defend its citizens\Nagainst all external aggressors.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:59.55,0:59:03.34,Default,,0,0,0,,My feeling is,\Nhe is so profoundly committed to his oath,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:03.34,0:59:06.57,Default,,0,0,0,,he'll forego the next election,\Nhe'll forego anything,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:06.57,0:59:10.57,Default,,0,0,0,,because he knows he's answerable to God\Nfor the oath.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:10.57,0:59:18.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's see if that's so.\NWe have permission to confirm my intuition.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:18.38,0:59:21.57,Default,,0,0,0,,My intuition is correct.\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:21.57,0:59:23.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Third step in AA,\Nyou surrender your life to God.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:23.57,0:59:28.57,Default,,0,0,0,,You're answerable only to God.\NYou're not answerable to the poll takers.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:28.57,0:59:36.21,Default,,0,0,0,,You're not answerable to the politicians.\NHaving taken an oath of office
Dialogue: 0,0:59:36.21,0:59:40.21,Default,,0,0,0,,and sworn in the name of God\Nto uphold the Constitution,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:40.21,0:59:47.50,Default,,0,0,0,,he doesn't have any freedom to move.\NThat's how I see his moral position.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:47.50,0:59:54.09,Default,,0,0,0,,His moral position is he's pretty much stuck.\NYou're the doctor in charge of the case.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:54.09,0:59:58.19,Default,,0,0,0,,When you're the doctor on call,\Nand they call you for a hot appendix
Dialogue: 0,0:59:58.19,1:00:01.19,Default,,0,0,0,,at one in the morning,\Nyou're it.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:01.19,1:00:08.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, as a physician,\Nyou take an oath.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:08.65,1:00:12.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Many a time in my own career,\NI had to decide,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:12.84,1:00:16.84,Default,,0,0,0,,am I interested in my popularity\Nwith my colleagues?
Dialogue: 0,1:00:17.07,1:00:27.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Or am I answerable to God\Nfor fulfilling my duty to this patient?
Dialogue: 0,1:00:27.61,1:00:32.69,Default,,0,0,0,,And many of the techniques I used many years ago\Nwere not currently in favor
Dialogue: 0,1:00:32.69,1:00:36.19,Default,,0,0,0,,with the medical establishment.\NAnd I would look at the patient,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:36.19,1:00:41.90,Default,,0,0,0,,and I'd say,\Nis my obligation to be popular with them?
Dialogue: 0,1:00:41.90,1:00:48.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Will I be answerable on my deathbed\Nfor my popularity with my colleagues?
Dialogue: 0,1:00:48.01,1:00:53.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Or am I going to be confronted\Nwith the face of this man?
Dialogue: 0,1:00:53.65,1:00:58.28,Default,,0,0,0,,God says,\NI took an oath to serve this man,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:58.28,1:01:04.38,Default,,0,0,0,,and that is my oath.\NMedicare regulations and all,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:04.38,1:01:09.30,Default,,0,0,0,,aside the point.\NIt's very comical now.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:09.30,1:01:14.61,Default,,0,0,0,,What the government calls HIPAA regulations.\NYou're supposed to protect the privacy of your patient.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:14.61,1:01:19.23,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, it's so stupid.\NI've protected the privacy of my patient
Dialogue: 0,1:01:19.23,1:01:24.23,Default,,0,0,0,,with my life since I started practicing.\NIt's been done since the days of Hippocrates.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:24.23,1:01:27.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Now the government wants to come in and\Nmake it a law.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:27.23,1:01:29.23,Default,,0,0,0,,You have to,\NI say,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:29.23,1:01:34.15,Default,,0,0,0,,where have these people been all this time?\NWithout integrity,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:34.15,1:01:38.69,Default,,0,0,0,,you cannot be a great practitioner.\NSo integrity then is the rule.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:38.69,1:01:43.05,Default,,0,0,0,,You follow your oath.\NAnd if you want to change that,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:43.05,1:01:47.05,Default,,0,0,0,,then you have to disclaim that oath.\NYou turn in your medical license
Dialogue: 0,1:01:47.05,1:01:50.59,Default,,0,0,0,,and say,\NI will not abide by these rules anymore.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:50.59,1:02:00.44,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't worship God.\NI worship the Medicare rules and regulations.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:00.44,1:02:06.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Sometimes there's a difference between the two.\NAll right.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:06.03,1:02:09.03,Default,,0,0,0,,So one is integrous\Nso long as one states one's position
Dialogue: 0,1:02:09.03,1:02:13.30,Default,,0,0,0,,and then is aligned with it.\NWhat is non-integrous
Dialogue: 0,1:02:13.30,1:02:16.30,Default,,0,0,0,,is to make a statement\Nthat this is my position
Dialogue: 0,1:02:16.30,1:02:20.30,Default,,0,0,0,,whereas actually you're devious\Nand have a hidden agenda.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:20.30,1:02:25.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Some of the news media,\Nsome of them that are controversial,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:25.00,1:02:29.15,Default,,0,0,0,,I calibrated them\Nand they were higher than I thought they'd be
Dialogue: 0,1:02:29.15,1:02:33.15,Default,,0,0,0,,because he states you right in the beginning.\NStates right in the beginning.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:33.15,1:02:35.15,Default,,0,0,0,,This is my position.\NAnd from that position,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:35.15,1:02:38.34,Default,,0,0,0,,this is how it looks.\NThis is how it looks.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:38.34,1:02:42.44,Default,,0,0,0,,So he's not pretending that he's in the middle.\NHe's telling you,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:42.44,1:02:45.44,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm a conservative.\NI grew up in the Midwest,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:45.44,1:02:49.13,Default,,0,0,0,,conservative.\NAnd from that viewpoint,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:49.13,1:02:51.40,Default,,0,0,0,,this is how it looks.\NThat's integrous.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:51.40,1:02:57.51,Default,,0,0,0,,To say that you're unbiased\Nand that you're going to give
Dialogue: 0,1:02:57.51,1:03:00.51,Default,,0,0,0,,an absolutely accurate accounting of the news\Nand then give it a slant,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:00.51,1:03:04.51,Default,,0,0,0,,that is not integrous.\NAnd that's how some of the networks have gone down.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:04.51,1:03:08.94,Default,,0,0,0,,They've actually gone down in the last year\Nbecause pretending to be
Dialogue: 0,1:03:08.94,1:03:15.28,Default,,0,0,0,,objective where you're actually up to something\Nis what's called a hidden agenda.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:15.28,1:03:19.34,Default,,0,0,0,,So to be integrous,\Nyou can be as loony as you want.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:19.34,1:03:26.80,Default,,0,0,0,,All you have to do is state that.\NThere's nothing wrong with those positions,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:26.80,1:03:32.57,Default,,0,0,0,,whether they're practical or not is something else.\NIt's quite easy to look at it
Dialogue: 0,1:03:32.57,1:03:39.63,Default,,0,0,0,,from a Buddhic monastic viewpoint\Nthat no violence under any circumstances
Dialogue: 0,1:03:39.63,1:03:44.78,Default,,0,0,0,,is allowable.\NThat's fine
Dialogue: 0,1:03:44.78,1:03:49.09,Default,,0,0,0,,if you're living in a monastery.\NIf you're living on the streets
Dialogue: 0,1:03:49.09,1:03:53.65,Default,,0,0,0,,of various cities in the world,\Nit'll get you dead quickly.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:53.65,1:03:58.65,Default,,0,0,0,,So there's not a lot of old Buddhist monks\Nhanging around in the streets.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:08.59,1:04:12.59,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.\NSo if you want to be a real proponent for peace,
Dialogue: 0,1:04:12.59,1:04:15.98,Default,,0,0,0,,let's have a piece of work again.\NIf you want to be a real one
Dialogue: 0,1:04:15.98,1:04:28.40,Default,,0,0,0,,and not just one of these talkers,\Nthen you become a champion of truth.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:28.40,1:04:36.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Truth makes war impossible.\NWhen truth prevails,
Dialogue: 0,1:04:36.86,1:04:43.63,Default,,0,0,0,,no war is possible.\NSo what can we do
Dialogue: 0,1:04:43.63,1:04:47.92,Default,,0,0,0,,as a spiritual warrior\Nwho is pro-peace,
Dialogue: 0,1:04:47.92,1:04:55.38,Default,,0,0,0,,which I presume most people here are?\NAs you grow in spiritual maturity,
Dialogue: 0,1:04:55.38,1:04:58.38,Default,,0,0,0,,you start out as the,\Nooh, isn't it all nice,
Dialogue: 0,1:04:58.38,1:05:02.38,Default,,0,0,0,,pretty flowers and blossoms.\NWe'll sing hymns
Dialogue: 0,1:05:02.38,1:05:06.90,Default,,0,0,0,,and we'll pray for peace\Nand we'll tell him
Dialogue: 0,1:05:06.90,1:05:09.90,Default,,0,0,0,,that we want to be nice to him\Nand we want him to be nice to us.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:09.90,1:05:15.90,Default,,0,0,0,,And that'll work.\NSo we start out as spiritual innocents.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:15.90,1:05:23.09,Default,,0,0,0,,We're not aware of the downside of human nature.\NThen we become adolescent.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:23.09,1:05:28.09,Default,,0,0,0,,We become adventurous.\NWe have to explore all the New Age fairs,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:28.09,1:05:32.09,Default,,0,0,0,,get a million true psychic readings,\Nthrow the runes, the marbles,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:32.09,1:05:37.19,Default,,0,0,0,,the stones, the jacks,\Nwhatever.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:37.19,1:05:40.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Throw the cards,\Nthrow the picture card,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:40.19,1:05:44.51,Default,,0,0,0,,get your fortune told,\Nand we play around with that for a while.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:44.51,1:05:48.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, that's the adolescent exploring the world.\NYou know, let's see the world.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:48.78,1:05:52.09,Default,,0,0,0,,What goes on here?\NYou know, what goes on?
Dialogue: 0,1:05:52.09,1:05:56.46,Default,,0,0,0,,And of course in our teaching we say\Ndon't fool around with it,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:56.46,1:05:59.46,Default,,0,0,0,,stay away from it,\Nbecause you're naive,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:59.46,1:06:02.46,Default,,0,0,0,,you don't know truth from falsehood,\Nand you don't know what you're talking to
Dialogue: 0,1:06:02.46,1:06:06.42,Default,,0,0,0,,on the other side.\NThat which is non-integrous
Dialogue: 0,1:06:06.42,1:06:11.84,Default,,0,0,0,,wants to control and persuade others.\NWhen you think of it,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:11.84,1:06:14.84,Default,,0,0,0,,why would you want to persuade anybody\Nabout anything?
Dialogue: 0,1:06:14.84,1:06:19.48,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't care if anybody believes anything I say,\Nfrankly.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:19.48,1:06:22.48,Default,,0,0,0,,I only have one obligation.\NThat's to myself.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:22.48,1:06:28.57,Default,,0,0,0,,To speak of truth is I know it experientially\Nand through research.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:28.57,1:06:33.17,Default,,0,0,0,,That's my only obligation.\NWhether anybody buys it is irrelevant,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:33.17,1:06:39.21,Default,,0,0,0,,because on death's door I've done\Nwhat I see I am to do.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:39.21,1:06:48.07,Default,,0,0,0,,My only obligation is to myself.\NI'm only answerable to God.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:48.07,1:06:52.07,Default,,0,0,0,,So with that as a yardstick, then,\None becomes,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:52.07,1:06:58.59,Default,,0,0,0,,after the adolescent exploration,\None then starts to become more involved
Dialogue: 0,1:06:58.59,1:07:03.59,Default,,0,0,0,,in spirituality as a lifestyle.\NYou become sort of a champion of it.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:03.59,1:07:08.13,Default,,0,0,0,,And then we hit the level\Nof the spiritual warrior.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:08.13,1:07:15.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Spiritual warrior can be incredibly great\Nor incredibly horrendous.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:15.80,1:07:21.11,Default,,0,0,0,,The children down there with their hearts\Nand flowers are no threat to anything.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:21.11,1:07:25.25,Default,,0,0,0,,You can just wipe them out and dismiss them.\NThe warrior now,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:25.25,1:07:30.38,Default,,0,0,0,,you're getting enough power\Ndue to dedication and inspiration,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:30.38,1:07:35.71,Default,,0,0,0,,you can be pretty dangerous.\NSo the warrior now
Dialogue: 0,1:07:35.71,1:07:41.46,Default,,0,0,0,,can be either integrous or non-integrous.\NThere are black warriors
Dialogue: 0,1:07:41.46,1:07:47.57,Default,,0,0,0,,just as there are white warriors\Nspeaking certain kinds of language.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:47.57,1:07:55.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Those who stand for peace, then,\Nand integrity, then,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:55.61,1:08:03.84,Default,,0,0,0,,have to be the champions of truth.\NAnd at some point in some lifetime,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:03.84,1:08:10.30,Default,,0,0,0,,you may have to walk into the bullets.\NAnd it's a so what when you do it.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:10.30,1:08:15.40,Default,,0,0,0,,And then it's ecstasy on the other side.\NSo on the other hand,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:15.40,1:08:24.52,Default,,0,0,0,,there are warriors that go in the other direction.\NJihad is the spiritual warrior
Dialogue: 0,1:08:24.52,1:08:34.53,Default,,0,0,0,,of the dark side.\NDangerous, where is he?
Dialogue: 0,1:08:34.53,1:08:39.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Dangerous, religious wars\Nare the most bloody of all.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:39.63,1:08:45.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Here you are at 50.\NJihad is 50.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:45.71,1:08:51.73,Default,,0,0,0,,That is very, very dangerous.\NBecause when you think you're killing people for God,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:51.73,1:08:57.73,Default,,0,0,0,,you see, the minute you add for God,\Nnow there are no restraints or limitations.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:57.73,1:09:01.93,Default,,0,0,0,,For God, you can do anything.\NYou can kill millions.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:01.93,1:09:06.09,Default,,0,0,0,,You can torture people to death.\NYou can blow their heads off.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:06.09,1:09:10.76,Default,,0,0,0,,You can operate on them without anesthesia\Nwhile they're still alive.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:10.76,1:09:14.76,Default,,0,0,0,,The most demented things are now\Npermissive, permissive.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:14.76,1:09:20.50,Default,,0,0,0,,So that's where the danger lies in this world.\NThe danger is not Iraq and Saddam Hussein
Dialogue: 0,1:09:20.50,1:09:24.52,Default,,0,0,0,,and all those others.\NThose are nobodies in the overall
Dialogue: 0,1:09:24.52,1:09:29.52,Default,,0,0,0,,historical evolution of consciousness.\NNow here's what's going to hold up mankind right here.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:29.52,1:09:37.90,Default,,0,0,0,,And I don't know how they're going to get over it.\NIf you polarize a good part of the world's population
Dialogue: 0,1:09:37.90,1:09:41.90,Default,,0,0,0,,in religious war,\Nnow you're going back in history,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:41.90,1:09:45.90,Default,,0,0,0,,you know, close to 2000 years,\Nthe great religious wars of Islam,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:45.90,1:09:49.90,Default,,0,0,0,,et cetera,\Npitting Christians and others,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:49.90,1:09:57.10,Default,,0,0,0,,anybody who's not a believer\Nof whatever they believe.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:57.10,1:10:01.93,Default,,0,0,0,,So the human mind, then,\Nis easily programmed.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:01.93,1:10:08.26,Default,,0,0,0,,So a person who is really pro-peace, then,\Nbecomes a champion of truth.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:08.26,1:10:13.26,Default,,0,0,0,,There's only one guidepost to reach enlightenment,\Nand it's the core of all the lectures
Dialogue: 0,1:10:13.26,1:10:17.42,Default,,0,0,0,,and teachings and writings.\NThere's only one thing you can trust,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:17.42,1:10:21.57,Default,,0,0,0,,and that is truth itself.\NThat's all you can trust.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:21.57,1:10:24.81,Default,,0,0,0,,All the good books,\Nyou can go to any spiritual bookshop,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:24.81,1:10:27.81,Default,,0,0,0,,it's lined with good books.\NLined with them.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:27.81,1:10:32.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Dozens of mantras and physical exercises.\NBreathe in here,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:32.51,1:10:36.51,Default,,0,0,0,,now run the energy down your left leg,\Nnow go out your left nostril,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:36.51,1:10:40.51,Default,,0,0,0,,and pray to the angel,\Nand chant,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:40.51,1:10:45.85,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, you know what I mean?\NAnd they charge big bucks for those things,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:45.85,1:10:51.39,Default,,0,0,0,,and the next level will cost you\Nanother couple hundred.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:51.39,1:10:55.28,Default,,0,0,0,,And then after that,\Nit'll cost you another 500.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:55.28,1:11:00.97,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.\NThere is absolutely no guidepost at all
Dialogue: 0,1:11:00.97,1:11:04.97,Default,,0,0,0,,in the world we live in\Nwith the human mind,
Dialogue: 0,1:11:04.97,1:11:08.02,Default,,0,0,0,,other than to know\Nthe absolute truth of something.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:08.02,1:11:15.80,Default,,0,0,0,,The human mind is not capable\Nof knowing truth.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:15.80,1:11:20.14,Default,,0,0,0,,So the way to peace, then,\Nbegins with humility.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:20.14,1:11:27.13,Default,,0,0,0,,The human mind is not capable\Nof knowing truth from falsehood.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:27.13,1:11:32.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, we can't hate anybody,\Nbecause if they get caught in a bad place,
Dialogue: 0,1:11:32.13,1:11:37.82,Default,,0,0,0,,these jihad people are caught in a bad place.\NThey're caught in the spleen.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:37.82,1:11:43.77,Default,,0,0,0,,How do you get to heaven and God\Nthrough your spleen?
Dialogue: 0,1:11:43.77,1:11:48.42,Default,,0,0,0,,You'll get to someplace,\Nbut it's not celestial realms.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:48.42,1:11:53.48,Default,,0,0,0,,We have names for the lower astral realms.\NSo those go to the lower astral.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:53.48,1:11:59.61,Default,,0,0,0,,That which really denies God\Nand blasphemes the name of God
Dialogue: 0,1:11:59.61,1:12:07.18,Default,,0,0,0,,by labeling evil,\Nas divine.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:07.18,1:12:12.81,Default,,0,0,0,,The ultimate darkness\Nis to label truth as falsehood,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:12.81,1:12:22.27,Default,,0,0,0,,to deny God and substitute the opposite.\NGod is not found through the spleen.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:22.27,1:12:29.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's see if that's a fact.\NGod is not found through the spleen.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:29.15,1:12:35.85,Default,,0,0,0,,God is not found through the spleen.\NYou cannot find God through hatred,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:35.85,1:12:42.13,Default,,0,0,0,,through killing people,\Nthrough demonizing people,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:42.13,1:12:47.82,Default,,0,0,0,,by hating people.\NSo should we hate jihad people?
Dialogue: 0,1:12:47.82,1:12:51.78,Default,,0,0,0,,No.\NWhy would we hate them?
Dialogue: 0,1:12:51.78,1:12:55.78,Default,,0,0,0,,The Hitler Youth under Hitler.\NYou ever watch any of those great documentaries
Dialogue: 0,1:12:55.78,1:12:59.10,Default,,0,0,0,,on the History Channel?\NYou end up with a great compassion
Dialogue: 0,1:12:59.10,1:13:03.10,Default,,0,0,0,,for the German youth.\NIt was like the Boy Scouts.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:03.10,1:13:07.10,Default,,0,0,0,,They sat around the campfire\Nand sang wonderful songs,
Dialogue: 0,1:13:07.10,1:13:11.10,Default,,0,0,0,,and it was fantastic.\NAnd it was patriotic,
Dialogue: 0,1:13:11.10,1:13:14.50,Default,,0,0,0,,and it was togetherness.\NIt was,
Dialogue: 0,1:13:14.50,1:13:18.52,Default,,0,0,0,,you could form an image of yourself\Nas an adequate person.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:18.52,1:13:24.22,Default,,0,0,0,,It was incredibly great.\NExcept that it worshipped
Dialogue: 0,1:13:24.22,1:13:28.78,Default,,0,0,0,,a megalomaniac instead of God.\NThat's the only difference.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:28.78,1:13:32.78,Default,,0,0,0,,But as you watch how\Nthe whole culture was inculcated
Dialogue: 0,1:13:32.78,1:13:37.10,Default,,0,0,0,,into these belief systems,\Nyou couldn't have thought otherwise.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:37.10,1:13:42.10,Default,,0,0,0,,If I had grown up in pre-Nazi Germany,\NI would have become
Dialogue: 0,1:13:42.10,1:13:46.36,Default,,0,0,0,,a follower of Adolf Hitler, no doubt.\NHe was the savior of the German people.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:46.36,1:13:54.15,Default,,0,0,0,,He was going to right the wrongs,\Nand he was the savior of the
Dialogue: 0,1:13:54.15,1:13:56.89,Default,,0,0,0,,recognizing the existence of man\Nin the first place.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:56.89,1:13:58.35,Default,,0,0,0,,It was not a\Nreason and a means
Dialogue: 0,1:13:58.35,1:14:01.02,Default,,0,0,0,,to scream and shout\Nand go to the crossroad.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:01.02,1:14:05.63,Default,,0,0,0,,It was a plan.\NIt was an integralist.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:05.63,1:14:12.02,Default,,0,0,0,,So you can be an integralist\Nin your intention,
Dialogue: 0,1:14:12.02,1:14:14.02,Default,,0,0,0,,even though you are going\Nin the wrong direction.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:14.02,1:14:18.44,Default,,0,0,0,,And Krishna says that.\NThe difficulty there
Dialogue: 0,1:14:18.44,1:14:22.69,Default,,0,0,0,,with that society\Nis it was secular.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:22.69,1:14:28.96,Default,,0,0,0,,If they had acknowledged God\NAnd after the Great War, both sides ended up forgiving each other.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:30.75,1:14:37.77,Default,,0,0,0,,German soldiers and American soldiers became close buddies after the war.\NEverybody transcended the positionality.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:38.19,1:14:43.64,Default,,0,0,0,,We saw each other just as other human beings.\NI used to respect the kamikaze pilot.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:44.77,1:14:48.35,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought, here's a guy who's willing to give his life for his country.\NI mean, I've got to salute that guy.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:49.14,1:14:57.32,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, I may think his plane is going in the wrong direction, but...\NI mean, his intention was valorous, was it not?
Dialogue: 0,1:14:57.78,1:15:02.68,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, what more can you ask of a person?\NYou give up your life for your country.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:04.22,1:15:12.46,Default,,0,0,0,,So each person then, as Christ said, and as the Buddha said,\Neverybody, whoever, anybody has said,
Dialogue: 0,1:15:13.06,1:15:18.46,Default,,0,0,0,,that we end up forgiving people and we're compassionate\Nbecause we see the limitation of human ignorance.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:19.57,1:15:26.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Intrinsic to the whole structure of the human psyche\Nis the incapacity to tell truth from falsehood.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:27.84,1:15:32.60,Default,,0,0,0,,And for that reason, we are willing to...\Nforgive anyone, no matter how,
Dialogue: 0,1:15:33.77,1:15:42.52,Default,,0,0,0,,far from the truth they may appear to us to be.\NAll right, so we get to the level of the spiritual warrior.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:43.50,1:15:50.60,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, Bush is in a spiritual warrior.\NPowell is more to the heart of the spiritual warrior.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:50.60,1:15:57.61,Default,,0,0,0,,But that is carrying forth, let's say,\Nas he sees it, his Christian duty,
Dialogue: 0,1:15:58.00,1:16:02.68,Default,,0,0,0,,based on his oath of office, his integrity to himself\Nand to his fellow Americans.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:02.88,1:16:12.52,Default,,0,0,0,,And so one can have an opinion about it one way or the other.\NBut our job is not to have an opinion about things.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:12.64,1:16:17.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Our job is to try and avoid opinions.\NBecause if the way to peace is through truth,
Dialogue: 0,1:16:17.55,1:16:25.18,Default,,0,0,0,,then we have to know what truth is.\NAt first observation, we noticed that 78% of the world's population
Dialogue: 0,1:16:25.18,1:16:29.40,Default,,0,0,0,,is against truth.\NLet's have our calibrated levels.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:34.40,1:16:41.61,Default,,0,0,0,,From here up, the commitment is the truth of increasing degrees.\NFrom here down,
Dialogue: 0,1:16:41.88,1:16:45.43,Default,,0,0,0,,it's to falsehood.\NTherefore, you can see,
Dialogue: 0,1:16:46.97,1:16:53.52,Default,,0,0,0,,you want peace in a society, in a world,\Nin which close to 80% of the people
Dialogue: 0,1:16:53.52,1:16:59.90,Default,,0,0,0,,would rather have anything but peace.\NWhy is that?
Dialogue: 0,1:17:00.35,1:17:04.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Why? Because it's more important to be right.\NIsn't it?
Dialogue: 0,1:17:05.46,1:17:12.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Celebrities get up there, make idiots out of themselves.\NYou know, it's their big ego wanting to be right.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:16.30,1:17:30.35,Default,,0,0,0,,So we say, people like that can't help it.\NPeople would rather be right, even if it costs them their life.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:30.65,1:17:37.85,Default,,0,0,0,,The ego doesn't care anything at all about truth.\NIt cares about winning and being right at any cost.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:38.69,1:17:44.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Be right at any cost.\NAll right, let's have the calibrated levels of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,1:17:44.72,1:17:52.34,Default,,0,0,0,,because we're going to see where does mankind go then.\NSo first of all, only 20% of the population
Dialogue: 0,1:17:52.34,1:18:00.89,Default,,0,0,0,,even gets to the opening doors to truth.\NWhere you're committed to integrity greater than gain,
Dialogue: 0,1:18:00.89,1:18:10.67,Default,,0,0,0,,which is a solar plexus, winning solar plexus.\NAnd as you go down then, you go down through the pride,
Dialogue: 0,1:18:10.67,1:18:23.03,Default,,0,0,0,,arrogance, greed, fear, all the way down.\NVindictiveness, hatred, polarization.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:26.72,1:18:32.36,Default,,0,0,0,,We've been talking today mainly about the Middle East phenomenon\Nbecause it's in today's current news.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:33.13,1:18:38.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Today is spirituality and the world, so I feel obligated to.\NFulfill that title.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:41.25,1:18:49.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, what we've been looking at is the high side of life, folks.\NMiddle East calibrates at what?
Dialogue: 0,1:18:50.03,1:18:57.27,Default,,0,0,0,,What did we say, 140 or, huh?\NWe were talking about the Middle East.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:59.55,1:19:08.00,Default,,0,0,0,,What did we say it was?\NWell, the Middle East then is a region that calibrates at 110.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:11.14,1:19:16.68,Default,,0,0,0,,A festering appendix.\NThe decision of the government had to be
Dialogue: 0,1:19:16.68,1:19:19.25,Default,,0,0,0,,how long should we wait for the appendix?\NShould we wait until it erupts?
Dialogue: 0,1:19:20.10,1:19:22.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Like, how long should we wait?\NThat's what happened in World War II, World War I.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:22.57,1:19:26.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Or should we try and nip it in the bud?\NLike it or not, you've got to operate.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:26.68,1:19:32.25,Default,,0,0,0,,I think that's what his practical,\Npragmatic decision was.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:32.25,1:19:36.25,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.\NSo that's how the world looks at 110.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:36.25,1:19:42.85,Default,,0,0,0,,We look at Israel and Palestine, calibrate 180,\Nsomething like that.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:42.85,1:19:46.85,Default,,0,0,0,,You see that that war goes on and on and on.\NIt's going on since I've been on the planet, frankly.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:46.85,1:19:57.23,Default,,0,0,0,,What happens if we look at the really bad part of the world?\NWhat if we look at Africa?
Dialogue: 0,1:19:57.23,1:20:04.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Rwanda.\NCivil war has been going on there for decades.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:04.15,1:20:09.15,Default,,0,0,0,,The U.N. has the slightest interest\Nthat they slaughter each other,
Dialogue: 0,1:20:09.15,1:20:13.77,Default,,0,0,0,,cut each other's legs off,\Ntorture each other to death.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:13.77,1:20:17.89,Default,,0,0,0,,The main way of death in Africa,\Nwhich is at war all the time,
Dialogue: 0,1:20:17.89,1:20:28.52,Default,,0,0,0,,is to hack people in small pieces.\NThat's the best way.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:28.52,1:20:36.39,Default,,0,0,0,,So when we take sort of a calm, detached look at the planet,\Nwe see that
Dialogue: 0,1:20:36.39,1:20:40.48,Default,,0,0,0,,probably for karmic reasons,\Ncertain levels of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,1:20:40.48,1:20:44.48,Default,,0,0,0,,seem to congregate\Nand get themselves born
Dialogue: 0,1:20:44.48,1:20:48.84,Default,,0,0,0,,in various regions around the world.\NSee?
Dialogue: 0,1:20:48.84,1:20:55.97,Default,,0,0,0,,The elephant herds don't hang out in New York City.\NYou know what I mean?
Dialogue: 0,1:20:55.97,1:20:59.97,Default,,0,0,0,,That's been human nature.\NThe way of animal life
Dialogue: 0,1:20:59.97,1:21:04.06,Default,,0,0,0,,for 40 million years or more,\N400 million years,
Dialogue: 0,1:21:04.06,1:21:08.06,Default,,0,0,0,,is that groups tend to congregate\Nin certain places on the planet.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:08.06,1:21:13.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Right now, the darkest place\Nis really Africa,
Dialogue: 0,1:21:13.35,1:21:17.64,Default,,0,0,0,,and the Middle East is quite a bit advanced\Nfrom where Africa is.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:17.64,1:21:21.85,Default,,0,0,0,,In Africa,\NI forget what percent of children die
Dialogue: 0,1:21:21.85,1:21:25.85,Default,,0,0,0,,before age two or something.\NThey do survive. They probably have AIDS.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:25.85,1:21:29.85,Default,,0,0,0,,And it's doubtful that they'll live long enough\Nto die of malnutrition.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:29.85,1:21:35.23,Default,,0,0,0,,It's so staggering\Nthat it never hits the news.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:35.23,1:21:39.85,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't see television commercials\Nor television documentaries
Dialogue: 0,1:21:39.85,1:21:43.85,Default,,0,0,0,,on current life\Nat the bottom in Africa.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:43.85,1:21:48.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Probably couldn't get on TV.\NIt's just too horrendous to look at.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:48.64,1:21:53.35,Default,,0,0,0,,So we can look at 110.\N110 makes great news.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:53.35,1:21:57.51,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know what the media's going to do\Nwhen the war is finally over
Dialogue: 0,1:21:57.51,1:22:01.80,Default,,0,0,0,,and cleaned up.\NWe've got, what's her name,
Dialogue: 0,1:22:01.80,1:22:06.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Peterson.\NThat saved him.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:06.63,1:22:10.63,Default,,0,0,0,,The war came to an end\Nand happily they discovered Peterson's body
Dialogue: 0,1:22:10.63,1:22:14.63,Default,,0,0,0,,just in time to save the news media.\NWhat are we going to talk about now?
Dialogue: 0,1:22:14.63,1:22:18.92,Default,,0,0,0,,They squeezed every last little bit\Nof news out of that.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:18.92,1:22:22.92,Default,,0,0,0,,I was going to get a kick out of them\Nbecause they'll tell you something that happened
Dialogue: 0,1:22:22.92,1:22:26.92,Default,,0,0,0,,and then they'll tell you what they just told you\Nand then they'll tell you what they just told you
Dialogue: 0,1:22:26.92,1:22:30.92,Default,,0,0,0,,and they told you it's a repetition.\NThey're really squeezing the last
Dialogue: 0,1:22:30.92,1:22:35.65,Default,,0,0,0,,lemon out of the news.\NSo that's what we call
Dialogue: 0,1:22:35.65,1:22:41.00,Default,,0,0,0,,juicing a phenomenon.\NJuicing it.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:41.00,1:22:45.96,Default,,0,0,0,,There's nothing that suits\Nthe ego better than war
Dialogue: 0,1:22:45.96,1:22:51.59,Default,,0,0,0,,to really juice it.\NThe third chapter,
Dialogue: 0,1:22:51.59,1:22:55.61,Default,,0,0,0,,I think it was chapter four\Nof the current book I put out
Dialogue: 0,1:22:55.61,1:22:59.61,Default,,0,0,0,,took the longest to write\Nbecause it was
Dialogue: 0,1:22:59.61,1:23:04.06,Default,,0,0,0,,the ego and society.\NHow to look at society
Dialogue: 0,1:23:04.06,1:23:08.10,Default,,0,0,0,,and see it as a projection of the ego\Nso that like a student
Dialogue: 0,1:23:08.10,1:23:12.10,Default,,0,0,0,,you can impersonally and detachedly\Njust study it as a phenomenon.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:12.10,1:23:16.26,Default,,0,0,0,,And a great deal of what we've done\Nin these classes
Dialogue: 0,1:23:16.26,1:23:20.26,Default,,0,0,0,,is to just study\Nbehavior and its expression throughout history
Dialogue: 0,1:23:20.26,1:23:24.46,Default,,0,0,0,,from a somewhat detached\Nobjective view
Dialogue: 0,1:23:24.46,1:23:29.85,Default,,0,0,0,,just as we tried to diagnose\Nthe war this morning.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:29.85,1:23:33.85,Default,,0,0,0,,And what we see is an endless game\Nan endless game
Dialogue: 0,1:23:33.85,1:23:37.85,Default,,0,0,0,,the players in the game\Nand we see the different moves
Dialogue: 0,1:23:37.85,1:23:44.03,Default,,0,0,0,,that they can make.\NNow the position I played with the gentleman
Dialogue: 0,1:23:44.03,1:23:49.60,Default,,0,0,0,,I had the advantage\NI'm a street fighter
Dialogue: 0,1:23:49.60,1:23:55.30,Default,,0,0,0,,that means I can hit you from any direction\NI can move in any direction
Dialogue: 0,1:23:55.30,1:24:01.96,Default,,0,0,0,,on the board.\NI have no limitation.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:01.96,1:24:05.96,Default,,0,0,0,,You're dead already\Nbefore the fight starts
Dialogue: 0,1:24:05.96,1:24:11.93,Default,,0,0,0,,you haven't got a chance.\NSo I have unlimited movement.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:11.93,1:24:17.47,Default,,0,0,0,,So you look at the chessboard of life\NI have a unique piece
Dialogue: 0,1:24:17.47,1:24:23.68,Default,,0,0,0,,I can move in any direction\Nany time I want.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:23.68,1:24:29.31,Default,,0,0,0,,This piece over here\Nthe gentleman can only move
Dialogue: 0,1:24:29.31,1:24:34.81,Default,,0,0,0,,in this way or this way.\NSee how the gentleman
Dialogue: 0,1:24:34.81,1:24:39.65,Default,,0,0,0,,is already limited?\NI think the religionist, the bishop
Dialogue: 0,1:24:39.65,1:24:44.03,Default,,0,0,0,,he can't move this way and this way\Nhe can only move this way and this way.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:44.03,1:24:48.03,Default,,0,0,0,,So you see the limitation of motion\Nthe limitation of options
Dialogue: 0,1:24:48.03,1:24:55.72,Default,,0,0,0,,goes down.\NSo when we watch social phenomena
Dialogue: 0,1:24:55.72,1:25:00.26,Default,,0,0,0,,the world is the ego's game board\Nin which it plays
Dialogue: 0,1:25:00.26,1:25:04.68,Default,,0,0,0,,these different players\Neach one you have to see
Dialogue: 0,1:25:04.68,1:25:14.25,Default,,0,0,0,,what are his options, what's his upside\Nwhat's his downside.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:14.25,1:25:18.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Is somebody who calibrates at 130\Ngoing to honor
Dialogue: 0,1:25:18.60,1:25:30.56,Default,,0,0,0,,a contract?\NHitler signed the non-aggression
Dialogue: 0,1:25:30.56,1:25:36.10,Default,,0,0,0,,treaty with\NNeville Chamberlain
Dialogue: 0,1:25:36.10,1:25:44.42,Default,,0,0,0,,his intention was to keep it.\NAfter they signed
Dialogue: 0,1:25:44.42,1:25:49.02,Default,,0,0,0,,the whole thing\NHitler thought Neville Chamberlain
Dialogue: 0,1:25:49.02,1:25:54.38,Default,,0,0,0,,was a stupid idiot.\NHe thought he was a stupid idiot.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:54.38,1:25:58.94,Default,,0,0,0,,We're talking about war man\Nwe're talking about survival
Dialogue: 0,1:25:58.94,1:26:03.34,Default,,0,0,0,,we're talking about death\Nand this idiot thinks I want to
Dialogue: 0,1:26:03.34,1:26:09.98,Default,,0,0,0,,honor a piece of paper?\NLet's see how Lindbergh
Dialogue: 0,1:26:09.98,1:26:16.17,Default,,0,0,0,,and all that ilk\Nleads to the blindness.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:16.17,1:26:20.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's bring in the Trojan horse\Nit's just a horse
Dialogue: 0,1:26:20.48,1:26:25.93,Default,,0,0,0,,looks peaceful\Nand out comes the Jihad
Dialogue: 0,1:26:29.97,1:26:33.97,Default,,0,0,0,,So the spiritual warrior then\Nhas to give up naivete
Dialogue: 0,1:26:33.97,1:26:39.67,Default,,0,0,0,,the spiritual maiden\Ncan go around saying
Dialogue: 0,1:26:39.67,1:26:43.73,Default,,0,0,0,,oh isn't that wonderful\Nwe'll have hearts and flowers
Dialogue: 0,1:26:43.73,1:26:50.19,Default,,0,0,0,,and we'll sing songs\Nand wear long robes
Dialogue: 0,1:26:50.19,1:26:57.50,Default,,0,0,0,,the world doesn't change\Nthey don't have enough power
Dialogue: 0,1:26:57.50,1:27:02.32,Default,,0,0,0,,so the spiritual warrior now\Nhas to give up
Dialogue: 0,1:27:02.32,1:27:07.10,Default,,0,0,0,,has to give up naivete\Nand I warned you
Dialogue: 0,1:27:07.10,1:27:11.73,Default,,0,0,0,,as spiritual work takes you higher and higher\Nyou get into the 500's
Dialogue: 0,1:27:11.73,1:27:15.73,Default,,0,0,0,,and in the 500's\None can only see innocence
Dialogue: 0,1:27:15.73,1:27:20.85,Default,,0,0,0,,and love\Nthat's all you can see there
Dialogue: 0,1:27:20.85,1:27:25.10,Default,,0,0,0,,everything is beautiful\Neverything is spontaneous
Dialogue: 0,1:27:25.10,1:27:29.43,Default,,0,0,0,,the fear that there could be\Nanything else out there
Dialogue: 0,1:27:29.43,1:27:33.43,Default,,0,0,0,,is not thinkable\Nso the downside of the 500's
Dialogue: 0,1:27:33.43,1:27:37.59,Default,,0,0,0,,the bliss state\Nis to close your eyes
Dialogue: 0,1:27:37.59,1:27:44.02,Default,,0,0,0,,to the fact\Nthat this is not a celestial realm
Dialogue: 0,1:27:44.02,1:27:48.31,Default,,0,0,0,,we're living in\Nso the vulnerability then
Dialogue: 0,1:27:48.31,1:27:52.31,Default,,0,0,0,,comes about by naivete\Nby naivete
Dialogue: 0,1:27:52.31,1:27:57.97,Default,,0,0,0,,you can turn that off for a second\Nit comes about by naivete
Dialogue: 0,1:27:57.97,1:28:01.97,Default,,0,0,0,,wishful thinking\Naspirant then has to go through
Dialogue: 0,1:28:01.97,1:28:06.03,Default,,0,0,0,,some difficult times\Nand letting go of these illusions
Dialogue: 0,1:28:06.03,1:28:11.28,Default,,0,0,0,,letting go of these illusions\Nin order to
Dialogue: 0,1:28:11.28,1:28:15.67,Default,,0,0,0,,be a champion of truth\Nyou have to do things that
Dialogue: 0,1:28:15.67,1:28:19.67,Default,,0,0,0,,to the spiritual maiden\Nsound just awful
Dialogue: 0,1:28:19.67,1:28:24.09,Default,,0,0,0,,oh, how could you do that\Nhow could you take a knife
Dialogue: 0,1:28:24.09,1:28:30.97,Default,,0,0,0,,and cut open a person's belly\Nyou do
Dialogue: 0,1:28:30.97,1:28:34.97,Default,,0,0,0,,to save a life\Nyou gotta cut open the belly
Dialogue: 0,1:28:34.97,1:28:40.38,Default,,0,0,0,,and if you don't clamp them off\Nthey exsanguinate
Dialogue: 0,1:28:40.38,1:28:45.27,Default,,0,0,0,,right on the table\Nor they die of shock
Dialogue: 0,1:28:45.27,1:28:49.27,Default,,0,0,0,,and if you don't they die of peritonitis\Nso like the
Dialogue: 0,1:28:49.27,1:28:53.30,Default,,0,0,0,,like the physician, like the surgeon\Nthen the spiritual warrior
Dialogue: 0,1:28:53.30,1:28:57.30,Default,,0,0,0,,reaches the point\Nwhere you have to realize
Dialogue: 0,1:28:57.30,1:29:01.72,Default,,0,0,0,,that there are areas\Nwhere in almost a surgical precision
Dialogue: 0,1:29:01.72,1:29:06.86,Default,,0,0,0,,you have to be willing to transcend certain illusions\Nthey seem painful
Dialogue: 0,1:29:06.86,1:29:11.35,Default,,0,0,0,,but let them go\Nto reach spiritual maturity
Dialogue: 0,1:29:11.35,1:29:15.35,Default,,0,0,0,,by hanging out\Nin naivete
Dialogue: 0,1:29:15.35,1:29:22.89,Default,,0,0,0,,naivete is one thing\Nmaturity is another
Dialogue: 0,1:29:22.89,1:29:26.89,Default,,0,0,0,,we become more realistic\Nso we stand for then
Dialogue: 0,1:29:26.89,1:29:30.89,Default,,0,0,0,,the dominance of\Nspiritual truth as the way
Dialogue: 0,1:29:30.89,1:29:34.89,Default,,0,0,0,,to God, the way to realization\Nof the self, the way to enlightenment
Dialogue: 0,1:29:34.89,1:29:43.64,Default,,0,0,0,,the way to truth then\Nis to let go of positionalities
Dialogue: 0,1:29:43.64,1:29:49.65,Default,,0,0,0,,war and peace are neither good nor bad\Nyou can't say that to a normal
Dialogue: 0,1:29:49.65,1:29:53.65,Default,,0,0,0,,audience\Nwhat do you think about
Dialogue: 0,1:29:53.65,1:29:58.10,Default,,0,0,0,,or feel about war and peace\Nyou want me to be honest
Dialogue: 0,1:29:58.10,1:30:06.06,Default,,0,0,0,,they are all the same to me\Nit doesn't make any difference one way or the other
Dialogue: 0,1:30:06.06,1:30:10.06,Default,,0,0,0,,why?\Nbecause beyond perception
Dialogue: 0,1:30:10.06,1:30:14.06,Default,,0,0,0,,they don't have any particular reality\Nnor do they have any moral loading
Dialogue: 0,1:30:14.06,1:30:21.50,Default,,0,0,0,,ethical loading of goodness and badness\Nin the reality which is this instant right now
Dialogue: 0,1:30:21.50,1:30:25.50,Default,,0,0,0,,there is no war, no peace\Nno anything else
Dialogue: 0,1:30:25.50,1:30:30.55,Default,,0,0,0,,those are all programs and stories\Nyou know whether you go out of
Dialogue: 0,1:30:30.55,1:30:35.06,Default,,0,0,0,,a body like this bang\Nor you go out
Dialogue: 0,1:30:35.06,1:30:43.00,Default,,0,0,0,,what the hell is the difference\Npeople who have survived heart attacks
Dialogue: 0,1:30:43.00,1:30:47.00,Default,,0,0,0,,people who have had near death experience\Nknow what I am talking about
Dialogue: 0,1:30:47.00,1:30:52.65,Default,,0,0,0,,it's all the same folks\Nhappily I had a near death experience
Dialogue: 0,1:30:52.65,1:30:57.61,Default,,0,0,0,,in teenage\Nduring the war death didn't mean anything at all
Dialogue: 0,1:30:57.61,1:31:02.55,Default,,0,0,0,,there is this mind\Nwith what you would call sticking out
Dialogue: 0,1:31:02.55,1:31:06.55,Default,,0,0,0,,like this and starting to bump against\Nthe star of our ship you know
Dialogue: 0,1:31:06.55,1:31:10.61,Default,,0,0,0,,because you are going to blow up\Nany second you are going to just go up with
Dialogue: 0,1:31:10.61,1:31:15.51,Default,,0,0,0,,this fine thing\Nso all I am worried about is it is going to scratch
Dialogue: 0,1:31:15.51,1:31:19.51,Default,,0,0,0,,the paint on the side of the thing\Nand blow us all the kingdom come
Dialogue: 0,1:31:19.51,1:31:24.63,Default,,0,0,0,,you know what I mean\Nhey man get a boat hook and help me will you
Dialogue: 0,1:31:24.63,1:31:30.89,Default,,0,0,0,,no fear of death at all\Nso it is comical
Dialogue: 0,1:31:30.89,1:31:36.50,Default,,0,0,0,,so if you get outside of this instant\Nthen you have fear
Dialogue: 0,1:31:36.50,1:31:41.21,Default,,0,0,0,,I still see a few old patients that I have seen for umpteen years\Nthey are too old
Dialogue: 0,1:31:41.21,1:31:45.21,Default,,0,0,0,,they slowly die off so I just figure\NI will just wait
Dialogue: 0,1:31:47.90,1:31:56.32,Default,,0,0,0,,they are all as old as I am\Nso anyway
Dialogue: 0,1:31:56.32,1:32:00.32,Default,,0,0,0,,those that are walking in one banana peel\NI tell them look call me for the next appointment
Dialogue: 0,1:32:06.71,1:32:10.86,Default,,0,0,0,,so one of them\Nof course I adore them all
Dialogue: 0,1:32:10.86,1:32:15.22,Default,,0,0,0,,that is why I don't chuck them all\NI adore them
Dialogue: 0,1:32:15.22,1:32:19.38,Default,,0,0,0,,this old guy is sitting there\Nand he has got this oxygen tank
Dialogue: 0,1:32:19.38,1:32:23.38,Default,,0,0,0,,he has got his oxygen tank\Nand he is older than nails older than dirt
Dialogue: 0,1:32:23.38,1:32:27.38,Default,,0,0,0,,she calls me older than dirt\Ndeficit post and older than dirt
Dialogue: 0,1:32:27.38,1:32:31.57,Default,,0,0,0,,she tells all the nurses\Nso anyway he is older than dirt
Dialogue: 0,1:32:31.57,1:32:35.64,Default,,0,0,0,,and he comes in and he has got his oxygen tank\Nand he has got this thing around his nose
Dialogue: 0,1:32:35.64,1:32:39.64,Default,,0,0,0,,and he sits down and he says\Nyou got a light
Dialogue: 0,1:32:39.64,1:32:43.64,Default,,0,0,0,,I said yeah\Nhe put his cigarette in his mouth
Dialogue: 0,1:32:43.64,1:32:47.64,Default,,0,0,0,,and I said\Nare we going to blow up
Dialogue: 0,1:32:47.64,1:32:52.78,Default,,0,0,0,,he says I don't think so\NI said ok
Dialogue: 0,1:32:52.78,1:32:58.10,Default,,0,0,0,,he didn't think so\NI suppose you should shut off the oxygen before hand
Dialogue: 0,1:32:58.10,1:33:02.61,Default,,0,0,0,,I am sure it has got a\Ngot a warning on the tank
Dialogue: 0,1:33:02.61,1:33:10.14,Default,,0,0,0,,I said what does it say on the tank\Nhe says I don't know I never read it
Dialogue: 0,1:33:10.14,1:33:20.92,Default,,0,0,0,,the manufacturer I am sure doesn't want to get sued\Nif we blow each other up
Dialogue: 0,1:33:20.92,1:33:26.17,Default,,0,0,0,,but it is that living in the moment\Nyou see
Dialogue: 0,1:33:26.17,1:33:30.17,Default,,0,0,0,,and it really didn't make any difference\Nif we both went sky high
Dialogue: 0,1:33:30.17,1:33:34.61,Default,,0,0,0,,we went sky high\Nyou got to get out of here somewhere
Dialogue: 0,1:33:34.61,1:33:39.35,Default,,0,0,0,,you want it slow and horrid\Nalright
Dialogue: 0,1:33:39.35,1:33:44.50,Default,,0,0,0,,so to die for one's cause\Nthen is
Dialogue: 0,1:33:44.50,1:33:48.56,Default,,0,0,0,,of course the hero of the war\Nis that young lady who got captured
Dialogue: 0,1:33:48.56,1:33:54.14,Default,,0,0,0,,and beat up\Nso she stands for something
Dialogue: 0,1:33:54.14,1:33:59.18,Default,,0,0,0,,that is\Nembedded in the core of America
Dialogue: 0,1:33:59.18,1:34:07.89,Default,,0,0,0,,the\Nwarrior but not just a warrior
Dialogue: 0,1:34:07.89,1:34:11.98,Default,,0,0,0,,a warrior with commitment\Nso the difference
Dialogue: 0,1:34:11.98,1:34:15.98,Default,,0,0,0,,between the killer and the warrior\Nis that the warrior is doing it for a principle
Dialogue: 0,1:34:15.98,1:34:20.25,Default,,0,0,0,,doing it for a cause\Ndoing it for something greater than themselves
Dialogue: 0,1:34:20.25,1:34:24.65,Default,,0,0,0,,and in World War II\Nthe greater than oneself
Dialogue: 0,1:34:24.65,1:34:28.65,Default,,0,0,0,,was not just one's country and all\Nand of course everybody wanted to win
Dialogue: 0,1:34:28.65,1:34:32.97,Default,,0,0,0,,but it was more a loyalty to one's\Nshipmates
Dialogue: 0,1:34:32.97,1:34:37.18,Default,,0,0,0,,the loyalty to one's shipmates\Nwas the
Dialogue: 0,1:34:37.18,1:34:42.17,Default,,0,0,0,,integrous core\Nif that mind blew up
Dialogue: 0,1:34:42.17,1:34:46.64,Default,,0,0,0,,we blew up\Nbut that didn't stop somebody else
Dialogue: 0,1:34:46.64,1:34:50.77,Default,,0,0,0,,from coming over and helping\Nso you see in the midst of war
Dialogue: 0,1:34:50.77,1:34:54.77,Default,,0,0,0,,that which\Nwe would think would be highly
Dialogue: 0,1:34:54.77,1:34:58.93,Default,,0,0,0,,you know not really a very spiritual\Nkind of a place
Dialogue: 0,1:34:58.93,1:35:03.51,Default,,0,0,0,,the midst of war is sacred indeed\Nin the midst of war
Dialogue: 0,1:35:03.51,1:35:08.40,Default,,0,0,0,,is sacred\Nthe midst of war is where a bonding goes on
Dialogue: 0,1:35:08.40,1:35:14.93,Default,,0,0,0,,of a lifetime\Nof those shipmates
Dialogue: 0,1:35:14.93,1:35:22.34,Default,,0,0,0,,sixty years ago or whatever it is\Nthose that still
Dialogue: 0,1:35:22.34,1:35:26.38,Default,,0,0,0,,remain\Nare the same as they had always
Dialogue: 0,1:35:26.38,1:35:30.60,Default,,0,0,0,,been and I remember when they\Ncalled me up
Dialogue: 0,1:35:30.60,1:35:34.89,Default,,0,0,0,,they located each other\Nafter fifty or sixty years
Dialogue: 0,1:35:34.89,1:35:38.89,Default,,0,0,0,,everybody started to cry\Nand when you hear this person's voice
Dialogue: 0,1:35:38.89,1:35:43.02,Default,,0,0,0,,they say this is so and so\Nand instantly the tears would come up
Dialogue: 0,1:35:43.02,1:35:48.17,Default,,0,0,0,,and you see that veterans of World War II\Nwhen they're interviewed about the war
Dialogue: 0,1:35:48.17,1:35:52.86,Default,,0,0,0,,so you see that patriotism is of the heart\Nto not love your country
Dialogue: 0,1:35:52.86,1:35:57.47,Default,,0,0,0,,means to be dead\Nif you cannot love the source
Dialogue: 0,1:35:57.47,1:36:01.80,Default,,0,0,0,,of your survival\Nmy father and my mother
Dialogue: 0,1:36:01.80,1:36:05.80,Default,,0,0,0,,doesn't mean biologic\Nthose two people
Dialogue: 0,1:36:05.80,1:36:10.38,Default,,0,0,0,,it means to honor your heritage\Nthe evolution of mankind
Dialogue: 0,1:36:10.38,1:36:14.69,Default,,0,0,0,,is now expressing itself\Nand the karmic upside of the human
Dialogue: 0,1:36:14.69,1:36:18.94,Default,,0,0,0,,is that you've inherited\Nthat which is
Dialogue: 0,1:36:18.94,1:36:23.10,Default,,0,0,0,,the willingness\Nto share
Dialogue: 0,1:36:23.10,1:36:27.23,Default,,0,0,0,,to be responsible\Nto forgive each other when the chips are down
Dialogue: 0,1:36:27.23,1:36:31.90,Default,,0,0,0,,when World War II is over\Nall of us
Dialogue: 0,1:36:31.90,1:36:38.85,Default,,0,0,0,,forgive each other\Nwhat could he do except do his best
Dialogue: 0,1:36:38.85,1:36:46.72,Default,,0,0,0,,for the Weimar people\Nso we saw the basic integrity
Dialogue: 0,1:36:46.72,1:36:50.72,Default,,0,0,0,,and because we saw the ignorance\Nunder the integrity
Dialogue: 0,1:36:50.72,1:36:55.88,Default,,0,0,0,,where he willingly forgave each other\Nwe don't have any resentment
Dialogue: 0,1:36:55.88,1:37:03.81,Default,,0,0,0,,left about anything\Nabout any fact of war
Dialogue: 0,1:37:03.81,1:37:09.10,Default,,0,0,0,,so in the end compassion then\Ntakes us beyond war and peace
Dialogue: 0,1:37:09.10,1:37:13.77,Default,,0,0,0,,it brings us to the awareness\Nof our reality
Dialogue: 0,1:37:13.77,1:37:17.77,Default,,0,0,0,,that all that goes on there\Nthat brings itself out there
Dialogue: 0,1:37:17.77,1:37:25.06,Default,,0,0,0,,as human society\Ncan't help be what it is
Dialogue: 0,1:37:25.06,1:37:29.06,Default,,0,0,0,,at the moment it's being what it is\Nif it could be something else
Dialogue: 0,1:37:29.06,1:37:33.10,Default,,0,0,0,,it would be\Nthe fact that it isn't
Dialogue: 0,1:37:33.10,1:37:38.14,Default,,0,0,0,,means it can't\Nif the person with an IQ of 90
Dialogue: 0,1:37:38.14,1:37:42.69,Default,,0,0,0,,could get straight hundreds\Nin school he would
Dialogue: 0,1:37:42.69,1:37:46.97,Default,,0,0,0,,with an IQ of 90\Nyou're lucky to get straight C's
Dialogue: 0,1:37:46.97,1:37:50.97,Default,,0,0,0,,and that's all we expect of them\Nso you see
Dialogue: 0,1:37:50.97,1:37:55.27,Default,,0,0,0,,on this planet\Nwe share a common commitment
Dialogue: 0,1:37:55.27,1:37:59.65,Default,,0,0,0,,the karma of being a human\Nis staggering
Dialogue: 0,1:37:59.65,1:38:03.90,Default,,0,0,0,,just be a human\Ntherefore I honor and respect
Dialogue: 0,1:38:03.90,1:38:08.03,Default,,0,0,0,,any human being that walks this planet\Nbecause to be a human being
Dialogue: 0,1:38:08.03,1:38:12.03,Default,,0,0,0,,is extraordinarily difficult\Nextremely painful
Dialogue: 0,1:38:12.03,1:38:17.57,Default,,0,0,0,,extremely challenging\Nuncertain at every second
Dialogue: 0,1:38:17.57,1:38:21.57,Default,,0,0,0,,one second of inattention\Nand your car rolls over and you're dead
Dialogue: 0,1:38:21.57,1:38:28.22,Default,,0,0,0,,so we all live one second from death\Nmore people have died on the highways in Arizona
Dialogue: 0,1:38:28.22,1:38:32.22,Default,,0,0,0,,than have died in Iraq\Nthis last month
Dialogue: 0,1:38:32.22,1:38:36.22,Default,,0,0,0,,since the time the war's been on\Nmore people have been killed on the highway
Dialogue: 0,1:38:36.22,1:38:41.60,Default,,0,0,0,,in the US military\Nbut it's not dramatic
Dialogue: 0,1:38:41.60,1:38:45.60,Default,,0,0,0,,see how we just accept\Nwell death by automobile
Dialogue: 0,1:38:45.60,1:38:49.82,Default,,0,0,0,,that's not a big story\N50,000 people die a year
Dialogue: 0,1:38:49.82,1:38:53.82,Default,,0,0,0,,in automobile deaths\Nwhere's the excitement
Dialogue: 0,1:38:53.82,1:38:57.89,Default,,0,0,0,,where's the drama\Nwhere's the parades
Dialogue: 0,1:38:57.89,1:39:02.40,Default,,0,0,0,,there's a lot of different politicians out there\Nwith a big make wrong
Dialogue: 0,1:39:04.53,1:39:11.77,Default,,0,0,0,,so you see\Nthe tendency of the ego then is to
Dialogue: 0,1:39:11.77,1:39:15.93,Default,,0,0,0,,take a position\Nthen dramatize it
Dialogue: 0,1:39:15.93,1:39:19.93,Default,,0,0,0,,then put a lot of energy in it\Nit gets polarized against people who think differently
Dialogue: 0,1:39:19.93,1:39:26.61,Default,,0,0,0,,than you do\Nthe positions that people represent then
Dialogue: 0,1:39:26.61,1:39:30.71,Default,,0,0,0,,about the war\Nare reflective of their level of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,1:39:30.71,1:39:36.40,Default,,0,0,0,,we need a level of consciousness back again\Nalright we said 80% of the people live
Dialogue: 0,1:39:36.40,1:39:40.85,Default,,0,0,0,,below here\Nso if we calibrate people's level of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,1:39:40.85,1:39:44.85,Default,,0,0,0,,we can see\Nthey're not reflecting reality
Dialogue: 0,1:39:44.85,1:39:49.50,Default,,0,0,0,,they're reflecting their own level of consciousness\Npeople who live down here
Dialogue: 0,1:39:49.50,1:39:54.55,Default,,0,0,0,,come out of hatred\Nthese people come out of gain
Dialogue: 0,1:39:54.55,1:39:58.55,Default,,0,0,0,,we're going to reconstruct Iraq now\Nyou can see all the bottom feeders coming in
Dialogue: 0,1:39:58.55,1:40:02.55,Default,,0,0,0,,with those contracts\Nget them contracts
Dialogue: 0,1:40:02.55,1:40:06.55,Default,,0,0,0,,when the fight is going on\Nthey'll disappear
Dialogue: 0,1:40:06.55,1:40:10.55,Default,,0,0,0,,when it's time to start\Nwhen they're missing the pumps
Dialogue: 0,1:40:10.55,1:40:14.55,Default,,0,0,0,,everybody's out there with their hands out\Nso there you got the solar plexus in greed
Dialogue: 0,1:40:14.55,1:40:18.55,Default,,0,0,0,,you see how pride plays into the whole thing\Nhow rage, anger
Dialogue: 0,1:40:18.55,1:40:23.64,Default,,0,0,0,,how fear drives people\Nthen we have the courageous
Dialogue: 0,1:40:23.64,1:40:27.64,Default,,0,0,0,,you know\Nreally make the headlines
Dialogue: 0,1:40:27.64,1:40:31.82,Default,,0,0,0,,that girl will be a hero forever\Nthen you get into neutrality
Dialogue: 0,1:40:31.82,1:40:37.50,Default,,0,0,0,,which is beyond it all\Nthe position I gave to you before
Dialogue: 0,1:40:37.50,1:40:42.19,Default,,0,0,0,,sounds like neutrality\Nit's okay if we have peace, it's okay if we have war, don't bother me
Dialogue: 0,1:40:42.19,1:40:46.19,Default,,0,0,0,,the detachment\Nthen the willingness to enter in
Dialogue: 0,1:40:46.19,1:40:50.19,Default,,0,0,0,,and own the bottom side of it\Nthen the acceptance that this is human nature
Dialogue: 0,1:40:50.19,1:40:54.19,Default,,0,0,0,,so what we're seeing is human nature\Nexpressing itself out there on the game board
Dialogue: 0,1:40:54.19,1:40:58.57,Default,,0,0,0,,of the evolution of human consciousness\Nat this point
Dialogue: 0,1:40:58.57,1:41:02.64,Default,,0,0,0,,then we see the intellect and reason\Nthe intellect and reason is the doctor
Dialogue: 0,1:41:02.64,1:41:06.64,Default,,0,0,0,,it says\Nhow far can we let this appendix go
Dialogue: 0,1:41:06.64,1:41:11.06,Default,,0,0,0,,before we do something\Nthen we see love surpassing all of it
Dialogue: 0,1:41:11.06,1:41:15.38,Default,,0,0,0,,we see that love\Nis unlimited
Dialogue: 0,1:41:15.38,1:41:19.38,Default,,0,0,0,,unlimited love at 540\Nis rare, rare
Dialogue: 0,1:41:19.38,1:41:23.57,Default,,0,0,0,,it means to love everybody no matter what\Ncan we feel sorry for Ben Loudon
Dialogue: 0,1:41:23.57,1:41:28.14,Default,,0,0,0,,and all these people\Nit's pathetic isn't it
Dialogue: 0,1:41:28.14,1:41:35.96,Default,,0,0,0,,there's no point in hating somebody\Nthat is so weird
Dialogue: 0,1:41:35.96,1:41:42.17,Default,,0,0,0,,what's the name of that dragon\NKomodo dragon
Dialogue: 0,1:41:42.17,1:41:49.61,Default,,0,0,0,,let's see if we can find out\Nmy friend the Komodo dragon
Dialogue: 0,1:41:49.61,1:41:54.48,Default,,0,0,0,,calibrates over 40\Nif you have permission
Dialogue: 0,1:41:54.48,1:42:00.92,Default,,0,0,0,,45\Nthe Komodo dragon calibrates about 40
Dialogue: 0,1:42:00.92,1:42:04.92,Default,,0,0,0,,can you believe a guy going in there with his shoes off\Nto make nice with the Komodo dragon
Dialogue: 0,1:42:07.88,1:42:14.60,Default,,0,0,0,,he did it so help me\Nhe took his shoes off
Dialogue: 0,1:42:14.60,1:42:20.06,Default,,0,0,0,,and he thought he was tame\Nyou saw the game we started with
Dialogue: 0,1:42:20.06,1:42:24.64,Default,,0,0,0,,well I was the Komodo dragon\Nand he was the movie star
Dialogue: 0,1:42:24.64,1:42:28.64,Default,,0,0,0,,or the husband of the movie star remember him\Ntakes his shoes off
Dialogue: 0,1:42:28.64,1:42:32.64,Default,,0,0,0,,and hangs out with the Komodo dragon\Nand he's still living
Dialogue: 0,1:42:32.64,1:42:37.93,Default,,0,0,0,,beyond imagination\Noh let's have the war and peace
Dialogue: 0,1:42:37.93,1:42:42.65,Default,,0,0,0,,back again now that we have the Komodo dragon\Nwe really should have Komodo dragon
Dialogue: 0,1:42:42.65,1:42:50.57,Default,,0,0,0,,on there for contrast\Nso help me God there is a human being
Dialogue: 0,1:42:50.57,1:42:57.85,Default,,0,0,0,,that calibrates the same as the Komodo dragon\Nwe should really
Dialogue: 0,1:42:57.85,1:43:01.85,Default,,0,0,0,,enter into peace negotiations\Nwith him don't you think
Dialogue: 0,1:43:01.85,1:43:09.85,Default,,0,0,0,,I will invite him to a duel\Nme and Ben Loudon
Dialogue: 0,1:43:09.85,1:43:17.23,Default,,0,0,0,,will demonstrate\Nhow to do that
Dialogue: 0,1:43:17.23,1:43:21.72,Default,,0,0,0,,gentlemen would you like to come up again\Nwe'll have another duel
Dialogue: 0,1:43:21.72,1:43:34.35,Default,,0,0,0,,thank you\Nwe'll have a break
Dialogue: 0,1:43:34.35,1:43:36.35,Default,,0,0,0,,we'll have a short break and then we'll resume
